)@@G@@  (0101,('**    ')) . SIGN OFF@ @@@@          ER        EXIT$     @E@@@@RT
)@@G@@PCKERR    SA        A0,A5             . SAVE THE STATUS WORD@E@@@@      RU
)@@G@@    LXI,U     A0,0              . CLEAR FOR CONVERSION@F@@@@          DSRV
)@@G@@L       A0,3              . SAVE LEAST SIGNIF 3 BITS  @G@@@@          LSRW
)@@G@@SL      A0,3              . MAKE ROOM FOR FIELD DATA CHARS  @F@@@@      RX
)@@G@@    LDSL      A0,3              . PUT THOSE 3 BITS BACK     @E@@@@      RY
)@@G@@    AA,U      A0,'00'           . MAKE IT FIELD DATA  @F@@@@          JPRZ
)@@G@@        A5,BSPERR         . NEG A5 INDICATES I/O ERROR@G@@@@          LSSA

)@@G@@    JN        A5,$+3            . WE HAVE MSG SET FOR PACK$ ERROR @F@@@@SC
)@@G@@          LA        A1,('BSP   ')     . TO MAKE IT SAY BSP ERROR  @E@@@@SD
)@@G@@          SA        A1,IOMSG          . SET IN THE MESSAGE  @E@@@@      SE
)@@G@@    SA,T3     A0,IOMSG+2        . SET THE STATUS CODE @E@@@@          P$SF
)@@G@@RINT    (0200+IL,IOMSG)   . OUTPUT THE MESSAGE  @D@@@@          J       SG
)@@G@@  FREFIL            . FREE THE FILE @F@@@@BSPERR    SA,T3     A0,BSPMSG+SH
)@@G@@1       . SET THE STATUS IN THE MSG @G@@@@          P$RINT    (0200+BL,BSI
)@@G@@SPMSG)  . TELL THE USER ABOUT THE ERROR   @D@@@@          J         FREFSJ
)@@G@@IL            . FILE THE FILE @G@@@@PERERR    LX        A1,A5           SK
)@@G@@  . GET PERMISSION ERROR STATUS     @F@@@@          LX        A0,PERMSG,SL
)@@G@@A1      . INDEX INTO PRINT$ TABLE   @G@@@@          ER        PRINT$    SM
)@@G@@        . PRINT THE APPROPRIATE MESSAGE   @D@@@@          J         FREFSN
)@@G@@IL            . FREE THE FILE @F@@@@CSFERR    LR,U      R1,1            SO
)@@G@@  . DO TWO GROUPS OF SIX CHARS@F@@@@CSF1      LR,U      R2,5            SP
)@@G@@  . THIS COUNTS THE CHARS     @D@@@@          DSL       A3,3            SQ
)@@G@@  . GET A DIGIT   @F@@@@          SSL       A4,3              . MAKE ROOSR
)@@G@@M FOR FIELD DATA  @F@@@@          JGD       R2,$-2            . LOOP BACSS
)@@G@@K FOR MORE CHARS  @F@@@@          TZ        R1                . IS THIS ST
)@@G@@THE FIRST LOOP ?  @G@@@@          LA        A5,A4             . YES, SAVSU
)@@G@@E LEAST SIGNIF CHARS    @G@@@@          JGD       R1,CSF1           . GOSV
)@@G@@ BACK FOR THE NEXT HALJ WORD  @I@@@@          DA        A4,('00000000000SW
)@@G@@0')                                 . MAKE I    @E@@@@          DS      SX
)@@G@@  A4,CSFMSG+2       . SET IN THE MESSAGE  @C@@@@          P$RINT    (020SY
)@@G@@0+CL,CSFMSG)  . PRINT IT@D@@@@          J         FREFIL            . FRSZ
)@@G@@EE THE FILE @G@@@@NOFIND    P$RINT    (0200+NL,NOFMSG)  . TELL THE USER TA
)@@G@@IT AIN'T THERE    @E@@@@          ER        EXIT$             . NO FILE TB
)@@G@@WAS ASSIGNED@C@@@@RINFER    ER PRINT$ . RINF$ HAS SET UP MESSAGE  @E@@@@TC
)@@G@@          ER        EXIT$             . NO FILE WAS ASSIGNED@[@@@@$(2)  TD
)@@G@@@G@@@@FREE      +         0                 . SAVE @FREE CODE FOR FIFREETE
)@@G@@$     @F@@@@FILE      +         0D                . SAVE INTERNAL FILE NTF
)@@G@@AME   @ @@@@NOFMSG    'SPEC 1 NOT FOUND'  @ @@@@NL        EQU       $-NOTG
)@@G@@FMSG  @A@@@@CSFMSG    'CSF STATUS  XXXXXXXXXXXX'@ @@@@CL        EQU     TH
)@@G@@  $-CSFMSG  @E@@@@RMSG      'READ PERMISSION NOT AVAILABLE FOR FILE IN STI
)@@G@@PEC 1'@B@@@@RL        EQU       $-RMSG            .   @F@@@@WMSG      'WTJ
)@@G@@RITE PERMISSION NOT AVAILABLE FOR FILE IN SPEC 1'     @ @@@@WL        EQTK
)@@G@@U       $-WMSG    @A@@@@PERMSG    +         0200+RL,RMSG    @A@@@@      TL
)@@G@@    +         0200+WL,WMSG    @^@@@@BSPMSG    'BSP ERROR XX'@ @@@@BL    TM
)@@G@@    EQU       $-BSPMSG  @ @@@@IOMSG     'PACK$ I/O ERROR XX'@ @@@@IL    TN
)@@G@@    EQU       $-IOMSG   @A@@@@BUFL      EQU       3*1792+100+14   @B@@@@TO
)@@G@@BUFF      RES       BUFL              .   @^@@@@          END       ST  TP
)@@G@@_@@@@@TUS.EQ.0) GO TO 290     @#@@@)      CALL FDD    @#@@@)      CALL STQ
)@@G@@ERR   @[@@@)C     @B@@@)C     ANALYZE LOOK-UP TA*[S@@@*SDFF*@B@@@@      TR
)@@G@@    AXR$,1                       .  @^@@@[          $INFO     9 1 @[@@@@TS
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@.         RE-ENTRANT DBANK-LESS BSP USED BY 'PACK$'   @B@@@@TT
)@@G@@.         68-2 BSP REHASHED BY MIKE MCAMIS@B@@@@.         UOM COMPUTER STU
)@@G@@CIENCE CENTER     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.         CAN BE USED AS A NORMAL BSTV
)@@G@@P BY SETTING REP=0@D@@@@.         THIS GENERATES LOCAL DBANK STORAGE. IFTW
)@@G@@ REP> @D@@@@.         0, DBANK IS EQUF'ED OFF THE END OF PACK$    @^@@@@TX
)@@G@@.         SCRATCH AREA  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@REP       EQU       1         TY
)@@G@@        . MAKE IT COMPLETELY REUSABLE     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@          ONTZ
)@@G@@        REP>0             . FOR USE WITH PACK$ REP...DBANK FOLLOWS@E@@@@UA
)@@G@@                                      . PACK$ CORE AREA     @E@@@@PACK$SUB
)@@G@@    EQUF      1792*3+100,X8      . CORES USED BY PACK$@B@@@@          OFUC
)@@G@@F                         .   @E@@@@          ON        REP=0           UD
)@@G@@  . WHEN NOT A REP...   @[@@@@$(0). @D@@@@PACK$S    RES       14        UE
)@@G@@        . ITS JUST CORE @B@@@@          OFF                         .   UF
)@@G@@@H@@@@NEWSEQ    EQUF      PACK$S+1        . SEQUENCE NUMBER OF ENTRY TO UG
)@@G@@BE ADDED    @G@@@@LNKWDS    EQUF      PACK$S+2        . LINK WORDS FROM UH
)@@G@@PACKET MODIFIED   @D@@@@                                       . (2 WORDUI
)@@G@@S)    @G@@@@SEQNBR    EQUF      PACK$S+4        . SEQNBR OF LAST ENTRY LUJ
)@@G@@OC BY BSP   @G@@@@STAT      EQUF      PACK$S+5        . H1=TYPE  OF PTR UK
)@@G@@H2=POINTING ITEM  @E@@@@ITMLOC    EQUF      PACK$S+6        . DRUM ADDREUL
)@@G@@SS OF ITEM  @D@@@@                                       . (2 WORDS)    UM
)@@G@@@B@@@@X11SAV    EQUF      PACK$S+8        .     @G@@@@FCT       EQUF    UN
)@@G@@  PACK$S+9        . HOLD ADDR OF FCT AND A1 (PKT)     @D@@@@            UO
)@@G@@                           . (2 WORDS)    @B@@@@ADDR      EQUF      PACKUP
)@@G@@$S+11       .     @B@@@@SAVEX9    EQUF      PACK$S+12       .     @B@@@@UQ
)@@G@@SAVEX10   EQUF      PACK$S+13       .     @B@@@@$(1)      LIT           UR
)@@G@@               .  @B@@@@P         FORM      12,6,18            .  @B@@@@US
)@@G@@SKIP      EQU       0                  .  @F@@@@PFWORD*   '**PF**'      UT
)@@G@@               . PROGRAM FILE INDICATOR   @F@@@@SYSKON*   1792          UU
)@@G@@               . STANDARD START FOR TEXT  @B@@@@          DO        SKIPUV
)@@G@@ , PROC        .  @B@@@@FCYCLE*   +         5                  .  @B@@@@UW
)@@G@@SCYCLE*   +         5                  .  @B@@@@KET*      +         1   UX
)@@G@@               .  @B@@@@KAPT*     +         01700              .  @B@@@@UY
)@@G@@KCPT*     +         02100              .  @B@@@@KFPT*     +         0230UZ
)@@G@@0              .  @B@@@@KEPT*     +         02500              .  @B@@@@VA
)@@G@@SPACES    '            '               .  @B@@@@          DO        1-SKVB
)@@G@@IP , PROC      .  @B@@@@          END                          .  @C@@@@VC
)@@G@@          DO        1-SKIP ,             PROC . @B@@@@PFTID$    EQU     VD
)@@G@@  PROC               .  @B@@@@PFTIA$    EQU       PROC               .  VE
)@@G@@@B@@@@PTWT$     EQU       PROC               .  @B@@@@WFTI$     EQU     VF
)@@G@@  PROC               .  @B@@@@WPFT$     EQU       PROC               .  VG
)@@G@@@B@@@@ETIA$     EQU       RES                .  @B@@@@PFTIDX    EQU     VH
)@@G@@  END                .  @B@@@@PFTIAX    EQU       END                .  VI
)@@G@@@B@@@@PTWTX     EQU       END                .  @B@@@@WPFTX     EQU     VJ
)@@G@@  END                .  @B@@@@WFTIX     EQU       END                .  VK
)@@G@@@B@@@@ETIAX     EQU       RES                .  @B@@@@          DO      VL
)@@G@@  SKIP , PROC        .  @B@@@@          END                          .  VM
)@@G@@@B@@@@          DO        SKIP , PROC        .  @B@@@@ETIA$     EQU     VN
)@@G@@  RES                .  @B@@@@PFTID$    EQU       RES                .  VO
)@@G@@@B@@@@PFTIA$    EQU       RES                .  @B@@@@PTWT$     EQU     VP
)@@G@@  RES                .  @B@@@@WFTI$     EQU       RES                .  VQ
)@@G@@@B@@@@WPFT$     EQU       RES                .  @B@@@@ETIAX     EQU     VR
)@@G@@  RES                .  @B@@@@PFTIDX    EQU       RES                .  VS
)@@G@@@B@@@@PFTIAX    EQU       RES                .  @B@@@@PTWTX     EQU     VT
)@@G@@  RES                .  @B@@@@WPFTX     EQU       RES                .  VU
)@@G@@@B@@@@WFTIX     EQU       RES                .  @B@@@@          DO      VV
)@@G@@  1-SKIP , PROC      .  @B@@@@          END                          .  VW
)@@G@@@B@@@@PFTNLX    EQU       RES                .  @B@@@@UFTIX     EQU     VX
)@@G@@  RES                .  @B@@@@PFTISX    EQU       RES                .  VY
)@@G@@@B@@@@RPFTX     EQU       RES                .  @B@@@@PFTNL$    EQU     VZ
)@@G@@  RES                .  @B@@@@UFTI$     EQU       RES                .  WA
)@@G@@@B@@@@PFTIS$    EQU       RES                .  @B@@@@RPFT$     EQU     WB
)@@G@@  RES                .  @A@@@@. *** READ FILE TABLE INDEX ***     @[@@@@WC
)@@G@@RFTI*.@E@@@@          L,U       A3,12              . CLEAR OUT DATA AREAWD
)@@G@@@C@@@@          L,U       A2,NEWSEQ          . START  @B@@@@          LXWE

)@@G@@@B@@@@          WPFTX                        .  @A@@@@. *** PROGRAM FILECP
)@@G@@ TABLE ITEM SEARCH@B@@@@          PFTIS$                       .  @B@@@@CQ

)@@G@@TABLE @G@@@@          L,H2      A5,0,A2            . QUOTIENT DETERMINE DA

)@@G@@    J         RELT               . NO     @B@@@@          PFTISX        DW
)@@G@@               .  @B@@@@          ETIA$                        .  @B@@@@DX

)@@G@@ MATCH@B@@@@          TE,S3     A5,3,A2            .  @C@@@@          J EA
)@@G@@        RETYP              . NO     @B@@@@VERCK     DL        A4,4,A1   EB

)@@G@@***************   @ @@@@. *** THE LOOKUP ROUTINE ***  @ @@@@. **********KY
)@@G@@***************   @]@@@@LOOKUP.     @B@@@@          S,H1      A4,STAT   KZ
)@@G@@         .  @G@@@@          L         A2,SEQNBR          . ITEM THAT CONLA

)@@G@@  A5,READ            .  @B@@@@          LMJ       X10,READIT         .  MB

)@@G@@ EXIT @B@@@@X11S      EQUF      X11SAV,0,H1        .  @B@@@@X11SP     EQMN

)@@G@@IT    @#@@@@. ***EQUATES***   @D@@@@READ      EQUF      02000,0,U       NO
)@@G@@   . READ FUNCTION@E@@@@WRITE     EQUF      01000,0,U          . WRITE FNP

)@@G@@ACW       EQUF      4,A0               . PACKET ACCESS WORD @E@@@@DRUMADOA
)@@G@@    EQUF      5,A0               . PACKET DRUM ADDRESS@G@@@@DSBEG     EQOB

)@@G@@BUFFER@F@@@@DLENGT    EQUF      1,A3,H1            . CURRENT TABLE LENGTOG

)@@G@@@B@@@@CHANGE    EQUF      0,A3,S3            .  @B@@@@          END     OJ
)@@G@@                     .  _@@@@@>@@@@C@C@@@@@@@@@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@B@@@C      OK
)@@G@@    AXR$,1                      .   @[@@@C.     @ @@@C. WRITTEN BY KERN OL
)@@G@@SIBBALD     @[@@@C.     @^@@@C. CALLING SEQUENCE DEFS @[@@@C.     @F@@@COM
)@@G@@FRSENT    $EQUF     0,X11,H2          . LOCATION OF FIRST ENTRY   @D@@@CON

)@@G@@    $EQUF     5,X11             .   @[#@@C.     @[@@@C.     @#@@@C. MAINOS
)@@G@@ ITEM DEFS  @[@@@C.     @E@@@CMQUAL     $EQUF     1,A1              . MAOT
)@@G@@IN ITEM QUALIFIER @E@@@CMFILE     $EQUF     3,A1              . MAIN ITEOU

)@@G@@MBER  @H@@@CMPACK     $EQUF     16,A1             . MAIN ITEM PACKID FOROX

)@@G@@M CREATION TIME   @F@@@GMLREF     $EQUF     18,A1             . MAIN ITEPA
)@@G@@M LAST REFERENCE  @[@@@C.     @ @@@C. DEFS FOR THE SAVE PACKET    @[@@@CPB
)@@G@@.     @D@@@CFL        $EQUF     0,,H2             . FORWARD LINK  @D@@@CPC
)@@G@@BL        $EQUF     0,,H1             . BACK LINK     @E@@@CSQUAL     $EPD
)@@G@@QUF     1,A0              . LINK PACKET QUALIFER@G@@@CSFILEN    $EQUF   PE
)@@G@@  1,A0              . FILENAME ONLY SAVE LOCATION     @E@@@CSPACK     $EPF
)@@G@@QUF     1,A0              . PACKID SAVE LOCATION@G@@@CSACCT     $EQUF   PG
)@@G@@  1,A0              . ACCOUNT NUMBER SAVE LOCATION    @F@@@CSPROJ     $EPH
)@@G@@QUF     1,A0              . PROJECT SAVE LOCATION     @I@@@CSFILE     $EPI

)@@G@@@G@@@CSACYC     $EQUF     5,A0              . LINK PACKET ABSOLUTE FCYCLPK
)@@G@@E     @F@@@CSADDR     $EQUF     1,A0              . ABSOLUTE DRUM ADDRESPL
)@@G@@S     @D@@@GSTIME     $EQUF     1,A0              . TIME STAMP    @[[@@CPM
)@@G@@.     @B@@@CENTX11    RES       1                 .   @[@@@C$(1). @[@@@CPN
)@@G@@.     @C@@@C. THIS SUBROUTINE IS CALLED FOR EACH FILE TO BE @D@@@C. PRINPO
)@@G@@TED. IT IS PASSED THE MAIN ITEM. THE APPROPRIATE@D@@@C. INFORMATION IS TPP
)@@G@@HEN SAVED IN CORE AND CHAINED INTO  @^@@@C. A DOUBLY LINKED LIST. @[@@@CPQ
)@@G@@.     @^@@@C.         LMJ X11,MAKENT@A@@@C.         +         HEAD OF LIPR
)@@G@@ST    @A@@@C.         +         SORT KEY CODE   @A@@@C.         +       PS
)@@G@@  SIZE OF SORT KEY@ @@@C.         +         MAIN ITEM @C@@@C.         + PT
)@@G@@        ABS DRUM ADDR OF MAIN ITEM  @#@@@C.         <RETURN>@[@@@C.     PU
)@@G@@@]@@@CMAKENT*.    @C@@@C          S         X11,ENTX11        . SAVE X11PV
)@@G@@@G@@@C          L,U       A0,2              . GET ENTRY SIZE (LINKS AND PW

)@@G@@        X11,ENTX11        . RESTORE X11 - IMPORTANT   @[@@@C.     @ @@@CPZ

)@@G@@RSENT         . GET ADDRESS OF FIRST ENTRY@E@@@C          L         A2,FQB
)@@G@@L,A1          . GET ITS FORWARD LINK@E@@@C          S         A2,FL,A0  QC
)@@G@@        . SET IN THIS ENTRY   @G]@@C          S         A1,BL,A0        QD
)@@G@@  . SET BACK LINK IN THIS ENTRY     @E@@@C          S         A0,FL,A1  QE
)@@G@@        . LINK IN THIS ENTRY  @E@@@C          S         A0,BL,A2        QF
)@@G@@  . SET NEW BACK LINK   @F@@@C          L         A1,MAIN           . GEQG
)@@G@@T ADDRESS OF MAIN ITEM  @F@@@C          L         A4,ADADDR         . GEQH
)@@G@@T ABSOLUTE DRUM ADDRESS @G@@@C          S         A4,SADDR          . SAQI
)@@G@@VE MAIN ITEM ADDRESS FOR LATER@D@@@C          A,U       A0,1            QJ
)@@G@@  . BUMP ADDRESS .@[@@@C.     @E@@@C          L         A2,SORTCOD      QK
)@@G@@  . GET SORT CODE KEY   @E@@@C          S         A2,MAKCOD         . INQL
)@@G@@TO INTERNAL CELL  @E@@@CMAKNXT    L         A3,MAKCOD         . GET NEXTQM
)@@G@@ KEY TYPE   @E@@@C          JZ        A3,MAKRTN          . RETURN IF NONQN
)@@G@@E LEFT@C@@@C          SZ        A2                . INTO A2 @^@@@C      QO
)@@G@@    LDSL      A2,6@ @@@C          S         A3,MAKCOD @F@@@C          TGQP
)@@G@@,U      A2,01             . CHECK THAT IT IS IN RANGE @E@F@C          TGQQ
)@@G@@,U      A2,06+1           . BETWEEN ONE AND SIX @E@G@F          TG,U    QR
)@@G@@  A2,SORTSIZ+1      . BETWEEN ONE AND SIX @B@@@G          TG,U      A2,SQS
)@@G@@ORTSIZ+1      .   @D@@@C          J         MAKNXT            . GET NEXTQT
)@@G@@ ONE  @F@@@C          J         MAKTAB-1,A2       . GO DO PROPER KEY ROUQU
)@@G@@TINE  @H@@@CMAKTAB    J         NAME              . SORT ON QUALIFIER*FIQV
)@@G@@LENAME(FCYCLE)    @E^@@C          J         QUAL              . SORT ON QW
)@@G@@QUALIFIER   @E@@@C          J         FILE              . SORT ON FILENAQX

)@@G@@ER    @E@@@C          J         PROJ              . SORT ON PROJECT     QZ
)@@G@@@D@@@C          J         PACK              . SORT ON PACKID@F@@@G      RA
)@@G@@    J         CREATE            . SORT BY CREATION DATE     @F@@@G      RB

)@@G@@        MAKNXT            . GET NEXT KEY TYPE   @[[@@C.     @[@@@EQUAL. RK
)@@G@@@D@@@E          DL        A4,MQUAL          . GET QUALIFIER @C@@@E      RL

)@@G@@        . SAVE IN FIRST KEY FIELD   @D@@@C          A,U       A0,2      RQ
)@@G@@        . BUMP ADDRESS  @E@@@C          J         MAKNXT            . GERR
)@@G@@T NEXT KEY TYPE   @[[@@C.     @[@@@CACCT. @E@@@C          DL        A4,MRS

)@@G@@        . SAVE IT @D@@@C          A,U       A0,2              . BUMP ADDRU
)@@G@@RESS  @E@@@C          J         MAKNXT            . GET NEXT KEY TYPE   RV
)@@G@@@[[@@C.     @[@@@CPROJ. @E@@@C          DL        A4,MPROJ          . GERW
)@@G@@T PROJECT FIELD   @E@@@C          DS        A4,SPROJ          . SAVE IT RX
)@@G@@AS FIRST KEY@D@@@C          A,U       A0,2              . BUMP ADDRESS  RY
)@@G@@@E@@@C          J         MAKNXT            . GET NEXT KEY TYPE   @E@@@CRZ
)@@G@@PACK      L         A4,MPACK          . MOVE PACKID TO KEY  @B@@@C      SA
)@@G@@    S         A4,SPACK          .   @D@@@C          A,U       A0,1      SB
)@@G@@        . BUMP ADDRESS  @E@@@C          J         MAKNXT            . GESC
)@@G@@T NEXT KEY TYPE   @[@@@C.     @]@@@GCREATE.     @E@@@G          L,U     SD
)@@G@@  A2,MCREATE        . GET CREATION TIME   @D@@@G          J         TDATSE
)@@G@@E             . AND CONVERT   @[@@@GLREF. @E@@@G          L,U       A2,MSF
)@@G@@LREF          . GET LAST REFERENCE  @H@@@GTDATE.                        SG
)@@G@@        . CONVERT TDATE SO IT SORTS PROPERLY    @D@@@G          L       SH
)@@G@@  A3,,A2            . MMDDYYSSSSSS  @D@@@G          LXM,H1    A3,,A2    SI
)@@G@@        . MMDDYYMMDDYY  @D@@@G          LSSL      A3,12             . YYSJ
)@@G@@MMDDYY0000  @G@@@G          LXM       A3,,A2            . YYMMDDSSSSSS -SK
)@@G@@- NOW IT WILL SORT@C@@@G          S         A3,STIME          . SAVE IT SL
)@@G@@@D@@@G          A,U       A0,1              . BUMP ADDRESS  @ @@@G      SM
)@@G@@    J         MAKNXT    @[@@@G.     @[[@@C/.    @D@@@CHEAD      $EQUF   SN
)@@G@@  *0,X11            . HEAD OF LIST  @H@@@CRDADDR    $EQUF     *1,X11    SO
)@@G@@        . RETURNED DRUM ADDRESS OF MAIN ITEM    @B@@@CDONE      $EQUF   SP
)@@G@@  2,X11             .   @C@@@CGETRTN    $EQUF     3,X11             . RESQ
)@@G@@TURN  @[@@@C.     @[@@@C$(2). @D@@@CMAKCOD    RES       1               SR
)@@G@@  . SORT KEY CODES@[[@@C.     @[@@@C$(1). @[@@@C.     @E@@@C. THIS SUBROSS
)@@G@@UTINE RETRIEVES THE ENTRY FROM THE DOUBLY LINKED@C@@@C. LIST SEQUENTIALLST
)@@G@@Y (PRESUMABLY AFTER SORTING). @F@@@C. ON RETURN A0 POINTS TO THE NEXT ENSU
)@@G@@TRY OR IS ZERO AT THE END.    @[@@@C.     @^@@@C.         LMJ X11,GETENTSV
)@@G@@@F@@@C.         +         HEAD OF LIST (CHANGED BY THIS SUBROUTINE)     SW
)@@G@@@H@@@C.         +         MAIN ITEM RETURN ADDRESS (CHANGED BY THIS SUBRSX
)@@G@@OUTINE)     @^@@@C.         <EOF RETURN>  @ @@@C.         <NORMAL RETURNSY
)@@G@@>     @[@@@C.     @]@@@CGETENT*.    @F@@@C          L         A0,HEAD   SZ
)@@G@@        . GET NEXT ITEM ON LIST     @D@@@C          JZ        A0,DONE   TA

)@@G@@PKT           . LENGTH OF EDIT PACKET     @B@@@@P         PROC          TN

)@@G@@1)>1 , ;      .   @B@@@@          L         A1,*1,X11         .   @B@@@@TV
)@@G@@          OFF                         .   @E@@@@          LMJ       X11,TW

)@@G@@  EOCTF$    2       .   @B@@@@EDECV*    LINK      EDECV$    1       .   VG
)@@G@@@B@@@@EDECF*    LINK      EDECF$    2       .   @B@@@@ECOPY*    LINK    VH
)@@G@@  ECOPY$    2,U     .   @B@@@@ECHAR*    LINK      ECHAR$    1,S1    .   VI
)@@G@@@B@@@@EPACK*    LINK      EPACK$    2,U     .   @B@@@@EMSG*     LINK    VJ
)@@G@@  EMSG$     1,U     .   @B@@@@ECOLN*    LINK      ECOLN$    0 1     .   VK
)@@G@@@B@@@@EFD1*     LINK      EFD1$     1       .   @B@@@@EFD2*     DLINK   VL
)@@G@@  EFD2$     1       .   @B@@@@ETIME*    LINK      ETIME$    1       .   VM
)@@G@@@B@@@@EDAY1*    LINK      EDAY1$    1       .   @B@@@@EDAY2*    LINK    VN
)@@G@@  EDAY2$    1       .   @B@@@@EDAY3*    LINK      EDAY3$    1       .   VO
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         CALL EPRINT(PKT,NSPACE)   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@VP
)@@G@@EPRINT*                               .   @B@@@@          S         X11,VQ
)@@G@@A4            .   @B@@@@          SZ        A3                .   @F@@@@VR
)@@G@@          L,U       A0,*0,X11         . ADDRESS OF EDIT PACKET    @D@@@@VS
)@@G@@          E$DITR                      . REOPEN EDIT   @E@@@@          E$VT
)@@G@@COLN                      . GET CHARACTER COUNT @E@@@@          S       VU
)@@G@@  A0,A5             . SAVE CHARACTER COUNT@A@@@@          E$DITX    .  CVV
)@@G@@LOSE EDIT   @E@@@@          L         A0,A5             . GET CHARACTER VW
)@@G@@COUNT @E@@@@          DSL       A0,36             . GET READY TO DIVIDE VX
)@@G@@@F@@@@          DI,U      A0,6              . DIVIDE TO GET WORD COUNT  VY
)@@G@@@F@@@@          TZ        A1                . IF THERE IS A REMAINDER,  VZ
)@@G@@@C@@@@          A,U       A0,1              .    ADD 1@G@@@@          TLWA
)@@G@@E,U     A0,23             . IS IMAGE LONGER THAN 22 WORDS?  @E@@@@      WB
)@@G@@    J         EPR000            . NO, GO PRINT IMAGE  @E@@@@          L WC
)@@G@@        A0,EPR020         . PRINT ERROR MESSAGE @B@@@@          ER      WD
)@@G@@  PRINT$            .   @G@@@@          L,U       A0,22             . SEWE
)@@G@@T IMAGE LENGTH TO 22 WORDS    @B@@@@EPR000                              WF
)@@G@@  .   @D@@@@          L         X11,A4            . RESTORE RETURN@B@@@@WG
)@@G@@          SZ        A3                .   @E@@@@          LSSL      A0,3WH
)@@G@@0             . SHIFT WORD COUNT    @F@@@@          L,U       A2,*0,X11 WI
)@@G@@        . ADDRESS OF EDIT PACKET    @D@@@@          L         A1,*1,X11 WJ
)@@G@@        . SKIP COUNT    @G@@@@          DSC       A0,12             . ALWK
)@@G@@LIGN SKIP COUNT, WORD COUNT   @E@@@@          LXM       A0,0,A2,H2      WL
)@@G@@  . ADDRESS OF IMAGE    @D@@@@          ER        PRINT$            . PRWM
)@@G@@INT IMAGE   @C@@@@          J         3,X11             . RETURN  @]@@@@WN
)@@G@@EPR010    . @G@@@@ '*** FOLLOWING IMAGE TRUNCATED TO 22 WORDS - SUBROUTIWO
)@@G@@NE EPRINT ***'    @B@@@@EPR020    +0100+$-EPR010,EPR010       .   @B@@@@WP
)@@G@@          END                         .   _@@@@@A_A__@A_A__@A_A__@A_A__@WQ
)@@G@@A_A__@A_A__@A_A__@A_A__@*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         T = TRACWR
)@@G@@KS ( MAINIT )     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         MAINIT IS A MAIN ITEM FROMWS
)@@G@@ AN EXEC 8 FILE DIRECTORY     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         T IS SET TO THWT
)@@G@@E NUMBER OF TRACKS ASSIGNED TO THE FILE   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          AXWU
)@@G@@R$,1                      .   @B@@@@          DIPROC    A2              WV
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@$(1)                                  .   @B@@@@TRACKS*   SZWW
)@@G@@        A3                .   @B@@@@          L,U       A2,*0,X11       WX
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@#          SZ        A0                .   @F@^@#          L WY
)@@G@@        A1,FLAG1          . CHECK FOR A TAPE FILE     @F@@@^          L WZ
)@@G@@        A1,FLAG3          . CHECK FOR A TAPE FILE     @B@@@#          TEXA
)@@G@@P       A1,TAPEF          .   @B@@@#          J         2,X11           XB
)@@G@@  .   @B@#@@          SZ        A0                .   @B@[@@          L XC
)@@G@@        A1,IMEDIA         .   @B@[@@          TG,U      A1,030          XD
)@@G@@  .   @B@[@@          TG,U      A1,040            .   @B@[@@          J XE
)@@G@@        2,X11             .   @B@@@@          A         A0,MT30         XF
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          A         A0,MT31           .   @B@@@@          A XG
)@@G@@        A0,MT32           .   @B@@@@          A         A0,MT33         XH
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          A         A0,MT34           .   @B@@@@          A XI
)@@G@@        A0,MT35           .   @B@@@@          A         A0,MT36         XJ
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          A         A0,MT37           .   @B@@@@          L XK
)@@G@@        A1,FLAG2          .   @B@@@@          TEP       A1,PGRAN        XL
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          LSSL      A0,6              .   @B@@@@          J XM
)@@G@@        2,X11             .   @#@@@@          END     _@@@@@@E@@@1      XN
)@@G@@    L         A0,FLAG3,X5       . GET CONSTRAINT*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@.     XO
)@@G@@@C@#@@.         CALL DTAPE ( BUFFER, STATUS , MCTBUF )@B@@@#.         CAXP
)@@G@@LL DTAPE ( BUFFER, STATUS )   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.         BUFFER IS A WOXQ
)@@G@@RK AREA DIMENSIONED AT 1812   @F@@@@.         THE FIRST TWO WORDS OF THIXR
)@@G@@S BUFFER CONTAIN THE FILE NAME@B@@@@.         OF THE OUTPUT DIRECTORY FIXS
)@@G@@LE.   @[@@@@.     @H@#@@.         MCTBUF IS A 1792 WORD BUFFER FOR THE MXT
)@@G@@CT FROM THE DIRECTORY TAPE.   @F@#@@.         THE FIRST WORD OF MCTBUF WXU
)@@G@@ILL BE 'SYMMCT' IF THE MCT    @A@#@@.         WAS SUCCESSFULLY OBTAINED.XV
)@@G@@@[@#@@.     @D@@@@.         STATUS IS SET BY THIS ROUTINE AS FOLLOWS.   XW
)@@G@@@G@@@@.                   0 - THERE WAS A TAPE FILE WITH AN INTERNAL NAMXX
)@@G@@E OF  @F@@@@.                       'DTAPE' ASSIGNED TO THE RUN.  THE TAXY
)@@G@@PE WAS@G@@@@.                       ASSUMED TO BE A SECURE DIRECTORY TAPXZ
)@@G@@E AND THE   @G@@@@.                       DGET$ PORTION OF THE TAPE WAS YA
)@@G@@COPIED INTO THE   @B@@@@.                       FILE  'DLOC'.     @G@@@@YB
)@@G@@.                   1 - NO TAPE FILE WITH AN INTERNAL NAME OF 'DTAPE'   YC
)@@G@@@C@@@@.                       ASSIGNED TO THE RUN.    @B@@@@          AXYD
)@@G@@R$,1                      .   @B@@@@          IOPROC                    YE
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@INAME     EQU       'DTAPE       '    .   @F@@@@BUFLEN    EQYF
)@@G@@U       1800              . SIZE OF SECURE TAPE RECORD@F@@@@OPKT      EQYG
)@@G@@UF      0                 . OUTPUT FILE CONTROL PACKET@F@@@@IPKT      EQYH
)@@G@@UF      OPKT+6            . INPUT FILE CONTROL PACKET @F@@@@BUF       EQYI
)@@G@@UF      IPKT+6            . BUFFER FOR SECURE RECORD  @H@@@@TEXT      EQYJ
)@@G@@UF      BUF+8             . BEGINNING OF TEXT IN SECURE RECORD    @B@@@@YK
)@@G@@$(1)                                  .   @B@@@@          LIT           YL
)@@G@@              .   @G@@@@DMTAPE*   SZ        A3                . NECESSARYM
)@@G@@Y FOR REENTRANT FORTRAN @E@@@@          SZ        *1,X11            . SEYN
)@@G@@T STATUS TO ZERO  @B@@@@          L,U       A2,*0,X11         .   @E@@@@YO
)@@G@@          L,U       A0,IPKT,A2        . ER FACIL$ ON DTAPE  @B@@@@      YP
)@@G@@    DL        A4,(INAME)        .   @B@@@@          DS        A4,IONAME YQ
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          ER        FACIL$            .   @D@@@@      YR
)@@G@@    TNZ       2,A0              . FILE ASSIGNED?@D@@@@          J       YS
)@@G@@  NOTAPE            . YES NO,NOTAPE @B@@@@          L,S1      A4,6,A0   YT
)@@G@@        .   @D@@@@          TG,U      A4,020            . IS FILE TAPE? YU
)@@G@@@D@@@@          J         NOTAPE            . YES NO,NOTAPE @F@@@@      YV
)@@G@@    L,U       A4,R$             . INITIALIZE INPUT PACKET   @B@@@@      YW
)@@G@@    LSSL      A4,24             .   @B@@@@          S         A4,IOSWRD YX
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          L,U       A4,BUF,A2         .   @B@@@@      YY
)@@G@@    S         A4,IOCADD         .   @B@@@@          L,U       A4,BUFLEN YZ
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          S         A4,IOWRDS         .   @F@@@@      ZA
)@@G@@    L,U       A0,OPKT,A2        . INITIALIZE OUTPUT PACKET  @B@@@@      ZB
)@@G@@    L,U       A4,W$             .   @B@@@@          LSSL      A4,24     ZC
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          S         A4,IOSWRD         .   @B@@@@      ZD
)@@G@@    L,U       A4,TEXT,A2        .   @B@@@@          S         A4,IOCADD ZE
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          L,U       A4,1792           .   @B@@@@      ZF
)@@G@@    S         A4,IOWRDS         .   @B@@@@LOOP      L,U       A0,IPKT,A2ZG
)@@G@@        .   @D@@@@          ER        IOW$              . READ TAPE     ZH
)@@G@@@B@@@@          L         A4,IOSTAT         .   @D@@@@          TNE,U   ZI
)@@G@@  A4,1              . END OF FILE?  @D@@@@          J         DONE      ZJ
)@@G@@        . YES,DONE NO   @D@@@@          TZ        A4                . STZK
)@@G@@ATUS ZERO?  @D@@@@          ER        ERR$              . NO, ERROR     ZL
)@@G@@@G@@@@          L         A4,BUF,A2         . GET HEADER FLAG OR DRUM ADZM
)@@G@@DRESS @D@@@@          TNE       A4,('SECURE')     . HEADER RECORD?@D@@@@ZN
)@@G@@          J         LOOP              . YES,LOOP NO   @B@@@@          LSZO
)@@G@@SL      A4,18             .   @B@@@@          SSL       A4,12           ZP
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          L,U       A0,OPKT,A2        .   @B@@@@          S ZQ
)@@G@@        A4,IODADD         .   @D@@@@          ER        IOW$            ZR
)@@G@@  . WRITE DRUM    @B@@@@          TZ        IOSTAT            .   @B@@@@ZS
)@@G@@          ER        ERR$              .   @F@#@@          L         A5,TZT
)@@G@@EXT,A2        . GET FIRXT WORD OF TEST    @E@[@@          TE        A5,(ZU
)@@G@@'SYMMCT')     . IS MCT IN RECORD?   @E@#@[          TNE       A5,('SYMMCZV
)@@G@@T')     . IS MCT IN RECORD?   @D@#@[          J         COPY            ZW
)@@G@@  . IT LOOKS GOOD @E@]@[          TE,H1     A5,('@@@MCT')     . IS IT L3ZX
)@@G@@6 FORMAT    @F@#@]          SSL       A5,18             . COULD IT BE L3ZY
)@@G@@6 FORMAT    @E@#@]          TE,U      A5,'MCT'          . PLEASE PAS THIZZ
)@@G@@S TEST@F@@@@          J         LOOP              . NO, GO GET NEXT RECOAA
)@@G@@RD    @G@[@@          L,U       A0,TEXT,A2        . YES, MOVE MCT TO USEAB
)@@G@@R BUFFER    @G@#@[COPY      L,U       A0,TEXT,A2        . YES, MOVE MCT AC
)@@G@@TO USER BUFFER    @B@#@@          LXI,U     A0,1              .   @B@#@@AD
)@@G@@          SZ        A3                .   @F@#@@          L,U       A1,*AE
)@@G@@2,X11         . ADDRESS OF USER BUFFER    @B@#@@          LXI,U     A1,1AF
)@@G@@              .   @E@#@@          L,U       R1,1792           . LENGTH OAG
)@@G@@F BUFFER    @C@#@@          BT        A1,0,*A0          . MOVE MCT@B@#@@AH
)@@G@@          J         LOOP              .   @D@@@@NOTAPE    L,U       A4,1AI
)@@G@@              .SET STATUS TO 1@B@@@@          S         A4,*1,X11       AJ
)@@G@@  .   @B@#@@DONE      J         4,X11             .   @B@@@#DONE      J AK
)@@G@@        3,X11             .   @B@@@@          END                       AL
)@@G@@  .   _@@@@@@G@@@@.         IF ASTAT IS SET TO 0, THE DGET$ WILL BE DONEAM
)@@G@@ IF THE ASSIGN    @G@@@@.         STATUS IS POSI*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@$(2)  AN
)@@G@@    LIT     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.                   EDPKT: INIAO
)@@G@@TIALIZED PACKET FOR EDIT$ ROUTINES  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.                 AP
)@@G@@  MITEM: MAIN ITEM FROM EXEC 8 FILE DIRECTORY   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.     AQ
)@@G@@    THIS SUBROUTINE EDITS INFROMATION FROM AN EXEC 8 MAIN ITEM    @[@@@@AR
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@$(1)      AXR$,1                      .   @E@@@@MIREG     EQAS
)@@G@@U       X9                . ADDRESS OF MAIN ITEM@E@@@@LINK      EQU     AT
)@@G@@  X10               . REGISTER FOR LINKAGE@E@@@@          DIPROC    MIREAU
)@@G@@G             . FILE ITEM FIELDS    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC    AV
)@@G@@  *0,2              .   @B@@@@BLANK*    NAME                        .   AW
)@@G@@@B@@@@          E$CHAR    ' '               .   @B@@@@          END     AX
)@@G@@                    .   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *1,5@B@@@@AY
)@@G@@IFBIT*    NAME                        .   @^@@@@          DO P(1)<4 , ; AZ
)@@G@@@B@@@@          L,U       A0,' '            .   @^@@@@          DO P(1)>BA
)@@G@@3 , ; @B@@@@          L,U       A0,P(1,4)         .   @B@@@@          L BB
)@@G@@        A1,P(1,1)         .   @B@@@@          TEP       A1,P(1,2)       BC
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          L,U       A0,P(1,3)         .   @B@@@@          E$BD
)@@G@@CHAR                      .   @B@@@@          END                       BE
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@@.     @C@@@@LISTMI                                . ENTRY   BF
)@@G@@@F@@@@          E$DITR                      . $P RE-ESTABLISH EDIT MODE BG
)@@G@@@E@@@@          E$COPY    12,IQUAL          . $P EDIT QUALIFIER   @B@@@@BH
)@@G@@          BLANK                       .   @E@@@@          E$COPY    12,IBI
)@@G@@FILE          . $P EDIT FILE NAME   @E@@@@          E$COLN              BJ
)@@G@@        . $P EDIT F-CYCLE     @B@@@@          L,U       A5,5,A0         BK
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          L,U       A0,1              .   @B@@@@          TNBL
)@@G@@E       A0,IACYC          .   @B@@@@          J         FCYC1           BM
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          E$CHAR    '('               .   @B@@@@          E$BN
)@@G@@DECV    IACYC             .   @B@@@@          E$CHAR    ')'             BO
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@FCYC1     L         A0,A5             .   @B@@@@          E$BP
)@@G@@COL                       .   @E@@@@                                    BQ
)@@G@@  . $P EDIT OPTIONS     @C@@@@          IFBIT     FLAGS,PRIVATE,' ','P' BR
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@          IFBIT     FLAGS,RONLY,'R'   .   @B@@@@          IFBS
)@@G@@BIT     FLAGS,WONLY,'W'   .   @B@@@@          IFBIT     FLAGS,GUARD,'G' BT
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          IFBIT     FLAGS,UNLD,'V'    .   @B@@@@          L,BU
)@@G@@U       A0,' '            .   @B@@@@          TZ        IASGCT          BV
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          L,U       A0,'A'            .   @B@@@@          E$BW
)@@G@@CHAR                      .   @B@]@@          IFBIT     FLAGS,EXCUSE,'X'BX
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          BLANK                       .   @F@@@@          E$BY
)@@G@@COPY    6,IACCT           . $P EDIT ACCOUNT NUMBER    @B@@@@          BLBZ
)@@G@@ANK                       .   @F@@@@          E$COPY    6,IACCT+1       CA
)@@G@@  . $P EDIT ACCOUNT NUMBER    @B@@@@          BLANK                     CB
)@@G@@  .   @G@@@@          E$DAY1    IRFTIM            . $P EDIT TIME OF LASTCC
)@@G@@ REFERENCE  @B@@@@          E$SKIP    -3                .   @B@@@@      CD
)@@G@@    BLANK                       .   @B@@@@          E$TIME    IRFTIM    CE
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          E$SKIP    -3                .   @B@@@@      CF
)@@G@@    BLANK                       .   @E@@@@          IFBIT     FLAG1,DISTCG
)@@G@@RYD,'D' . $P D MEANS DESTROYED@G@@@@          IFBIT     FLAG1,INCOM,'I' CH
)@@G@@  . $P I MEANS INCOMPLETE WRITE     @F@@@@          IFBIT     FLAG1,SECUCI
)@@G@@RE,'S'  . $P S MEANS SECURE REJECT  @E@#@]          IFBIT     FLAG1,CACHCJ
)@@G@@E,'D'   . DATA DISABLED FILE  @E@@@#          IFBIT     FLAG1,CACHE,'C' CK
)@@G@@  . CACHE DISABLED FILE @B@@@@          BLANK                       .   CL
)@@G@@@E@[@@          LA        A0,FLAG3          . GET SOME M.I. BITS  @F@[@@CM
)@@G@@          TEP       A0,MITEMF         . IS THIS A POST 32 M.I. ?  @G@[@@CN
)@@G@@          J         LEV32             . NO, USE SAME OLD GRODIE CODE    CO
)@@G@@@F@@@@          E$COPY    5,ASGNM           . GET ASIGN MNEMONIC FROM MICP
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LA        A0,FLAG3          . GET THOSE BITS AGAIN@F@@@@CQ
)@@G@@          TOP       A0,TAPEF          . IS THIS A TAPE FILE ?     @E@@@@CR
)@@G@@          J         FASTR             . NO GO COUNT TRACKS  @E@@@@      CS
)@@G@@    J         TAPE              . YES, PROCESS REELS  @F@[@@LEV32     L CT
)@@G@@        A0,IMEDIA         . $P EDIT EQUIPMENT TYPE    @B@[@@          E$CU
)@@G@@COPY    3,EQPTAB,A0       .   @E@[@@          L         A0,IMEDIA       CV
)@@G@@  . GET EQUIPMENT TYPE  @F@[@@          L         A0,EQPTAB,A0,S6   . $PCW
)@@G@@ GET CLASS OF EQUIPMENT @E@[@@          TNE,U     A0,'F'            . $TCX
)@@G@@ FASTRAND TYPE?   @E@[@@          J         FASTR             . $A YES,FCY
)@@G@@ASTR NO     @D@[@@          TNE,U     A0,'T'            . $T TAPE TYPE? CZ
)@@G@@@E@[@@          J         TAPE              . $A YES,TAPE NO,OTHER@B@[@@DA
)@@G@@          J         OTHER             .   @B@@@@FASTR                   DB
)@@G@@              .   @G@@@@          L         A0,MT30           . $P CALCUDC
)@@G@@LATE NUMBER OF GRANULES @B@@@@          A         A0,MT31           .   DD
)@@G@@@B@@@@          A         A0,MT32           .   @B@@@@          A       DE
)@@G@@  A0,MT33           .   @B@@@@          A         A0,MT34           .   DF
)@@G@@@B@@@@          A         A0,MT35           .   @B@@@@          A       DG
)@@G@@  A0,MT36           .   @B@@@@          A         A0,MT37           .   DH
)@@G@@@B@@@@          L,U       A1,4              .   @B@@@@          L       DI
)@@G@@  A2,FLAG2          .   @F@@@@          TEP       A2,PGRAN          . $TDJ
)@@G@@ POSITION GRANULARITY?  @E@@@@          J         POSGRN            . $ADK
)@@G@@ YES,POSGRN NO    @H@@@@          E$DECF                      . $P EDIT DL
)@@G@@NUMBER OF TRACKS ASSIGNED     @B@@@@          BLANK                     DM
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          BLANK                       .   @D@@@@          J DN
)@@G@@        PRNTIT            . $J PRNTIT     @G@@@@POSGRN    LSSL      A0,6DO
)@@G@@              . $P CONVERT POSITIONS TO TRACKS  @H@@@@          E$DECF  DP
)@@G@@                    . $P EDIT NUMBER OF TRACKS ASSIGNED     @B@@@@      DQ
)@@G@@    E$CHAR    '-'               .   @H@@@@          E$CHAR    'P'       DR
)@@G@@        . $P EDIT 'P' FOR POSITION GRANULARITY  @D@@@@          J       DS
)@@G@@  PRNTIT            . $J PRNTIT     @B@@@@TAPE                          DT
)@@G@@        .   @E@@@@          E$DECF    4,IRELCT          . $P EDIT REEL CDU
)@@G@@OUNT  @B@@@@          E$CHAR    '-'               .   @G@@@@          E$DV
)@@G@@CHAR    'R'               . $P EDIT 'R' FOR REEL GRANULARITY@D@@@@      DW
)@@G@@    J         PRNTIT            . $J PRNTIT     @]@@@@OTHER     . @F@@@@DX
)@@G@@          E$SKIP    6                 . $P SKIP EQUIPMENT DATA    @B@@@@DY
)@@G@@PRNTIT                                .   @^@@@@          BLANK     .   DZ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          L,U       A0,'U'            . $P U MEANS UNLOADED @B@@@@EA
)@@G@@          L         A1,FLAG3          .   @B@@@@          TEP       A1,REB
)@@G@@LOUT          .   @B@@@@          J         GOTUW             .   @G@@@@EC
)@@G@@          L,U       A0,'$'            . * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *   ED
)@@G@@@G@@@@          L         A1,WRTIME         . * * * * * * * * * * * * * EE
)@@G@@* *   @G@@@@          TNE       A1,('      ')     . * * * * * * * * * * EF
)@@G@@* * * * * * @B@@@@          J         GOTUW             .   @F@@@@      EG
)@@G@@    L,U       A0,'W'            . $P W MEANS WRITTEN INTO   @B@@@@      EH
)@@G@@    TNZ       WRTIME            .   @B@@@@          L,U       A0,' '    EI
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@GOTUW     E$CHAR                      .   @E@@@@      EJ
)@@G@@    IFBIT     FLAG3,BKUP,'B'    . $P B MEANS BACKED-UP@D@@@@      E$DITXEK
)@@G@@                          . $P CLOSE EDIT @B@@@@          J         0,LIEL
)@@G@@NK            . $E@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         CALL LISTM ( EEM
)@@G@@DPKT, MITEM )     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@LISTM*                              EN
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          S         X11,SX11          .   @B@@@@          S EO
)@@G@@        MIREG,SMIREG      .   @B@@@@          S         LINK,SLINK      EP
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          SZ        A3                .   @B@@@@          L,EQ
)@@G@@U       A0,*0,X11         .   @B@@@@          L,U       MIREG,*1,X11    ER
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          LMJ       LINK,LISTMI       .   @B@@@@          L ES
)@@G@@        X11,SX11          .   @B@@@@          L         MIREG,SMIREG    ET
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          L         LINK,SLINK        .   @B@@@@          J EU
)@@G@@        3,X11             .   @[@@@@$(2)  @B@@@@SX11      +0            EV
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@SMIREG    +0                          .   @B@@@@EW
)@@G@@SLINK     +0                          .   @B@@@@          END           EX
)@@G@@              .   _@@@@@@B@@@@          LXI,U     A2,1              .   EY
)@@G@@@H@@@@          DL        A4,OKMASK         . GET MASK OF ACCEPTABLE CHAEZ
)@@G@@RACTERS     @G@@@@      *[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@4.     @C@@@4.         MAIN PROFA
)@@G@@GRAM FOR CATALOG PROCESSOR    @[@@@4.     @B@@@4.         SEE DOC/CATALOFB
)@@G@@G FOR DETAILS     @[@@@4.     @[@@@4.     @H@@@4. ----------------  OPTIFC
)@@G@@ONS DOCUMENTATION NOT IN DOC/CATALOG  ----------------@[@@@4.     @[@@@4FD
)@@G@@.     @H@@@4.      F - ONLY PRINT FILES SPECIFIED IN SPEC1 THRU SPECN.  FE
)@@G@@THE FILES WILL    @G@@@4.          BE ASSIGNED AND A DREAD$ DONE TO GET FF
)@@G@@INFORMATION ABOUT THEM. @G@@@4.          THIS SAVES THE (RATHER LARGE) CFG
)@@G@@OST OF ACQUIRING A COPY OF THE@G@@@4.          MASTER FILE DIRECTORY IF FH
)@@G@@YOU ONLY WANT INFORMATION ABOUT ONE @#@@@4.          FILE.  @[@@@4.     FI
)@@G@@@G@@@4.      K - DISPLAY THE READ/WRITE KEYS OF PRINTED FILE NAMES (MUSTFJ
)@@G@@ BE   @F@@@4.          ENABLED BY SETTING THE TAG KEYON TO A NON ZERO VAFK
)@@G@@LUE)  @[@@@4.     @G@@@4.      V - USE THE MSCON$ FUNCTION DGET$ TO FETCFL
)@@G@@H A COPY OF THE ENTIRE  @H@@@4.          DIRECTORY INSTEAD OF THE SHORT FM
)@@G@@LIST FILES WHICH ARE CATALOGUED     @H@@@4.          UNDER THIS ACCOUNT FN
)@@G@@NUMBER.  THE SHORT LIST IS AQUIRED BY USING     @H@@@4.          THE UOMFO
)@@G@@ MSCON$ FUNCTION SDGET$ (CODE 7).  THE FUNCTION RETURNS     @H@@@4.     FP
)@@G@@     A LIST OF FILE MAIN ITEMS CREATED BY THE USER EXECUTING THE ER.    FQ
)@@G@@@G@@@4.          THE F2 GRANULE COUNT HAS THE NUMBER OF UNLOADED TRACKS FR
)@@G@@AND IF@G@@@4.          THE FILE IS CATALOGUED ON REMOVABLE DISK, THE FIRFS
)@@G@@ST PACKID IS@G@@@4.          IN THE WORD NORMALLY USED FOR THE LINK TO TFT
)@@G@@HE EXPOOL ITEM FOR@F@@@4.          THAT FILE.  THE USE OF THE 'V'-OPTIONFU
)@@G@@ WILL RESULT IN A @E@@@4.          SUBSTANTIAL EXTRA CHARGE TO THE CALLIFV
)@@G@@NG RUN.     @[@@@4.     @F@@@4. ---------------- END OF EXTRA DOCUMENTATFW

)@@G@@TBL)//2       . NUMBER OF ENTRIES   @[@@@4/.    @E@@@4.  THIS LOOP FETCHCW
)@@G@@ES DIRECTORY ITEMS, SUBMITS THEM FOR THE  @D@@@4.  PRINT/NOPRINT DECISIOCX

)@@G@@TEMS ARE ONCE AGAIN READ IN   @ @@@4. AND PROCESSED FOR PRINTING. @[@@@4DC

)@@G@@ LATER USE  @C@@@4UNL090    L         X11,UNLRET        . RETURN  @ @@@4RP
)@@G@@          J         0,X11     @[@@@4.     @[@@@4.     @G@@@4. THIS SUBRORQ
)@@G@@UTINE READS THE SECTOR POINTED TO BY A4.  THE CURRENT ITEM  @B@@@4.   ISRR
)@@G@@ SAVED IN THE SPACE AT LABLE 'SECTR'@[@@@4.     @B@@@4. CALL:   LA    A4RS
)@@G@@,<ABS ADDR OF SECTOR>   @ @@@4.         LMJ   X11,GETSCT    @[@@@4.     RT
)@@G@@@F@@@4. ON ENTRY, X5 IS ASSUMED TO POINT TO THE CURRENT DIRECTORY SECTORRU
)@@G@@@[@@@4.     @G@@@4. ON EXIT, A2 POINTS TO THE FETCHED SECTOR AND A0 HAS RV
)@@G@@THE FDSUBS STATUS.@[@@@4.     @C@@@4GETSCT                              RW
)@@G@@  . ENTRY   @G@@@4          LA,U      A0,0              . ASSUME NORMAL RX
)@@G@@RETURN FOR NOW    @F@@@4          LX,U      A2,28,X5          . BUMP UP RY
)@@G@@PAST CURRENT TIEM @F@@@4          TZ        OPT('F')          . DID WE DRZ
)@@G@@READ TO GET INFO ?@G@@@4          J         0,X11             . YES, A2 SA
)@@G@@POINTS AT NEXT ITEM     @D@@@4          SX        X11,GTSTRT        . SASB
)@@G@@VE RETURN   @E@@@4          LXI,U     X5,1              . SET INCREMENT SC
)@@G@@PART  @E@@@4          LX        A2,(1,SECTR)      . ADDRESS OF SAVE AREASD
)@@G@@@F@@@4          LR,U      R1,28             . NUMBER OF WORDS TO MOVE   SE
)@@G@@@D@@@4          BT        A2,0,*X5          . MOVE THEM     @G@@@4      SF
)@@G@@    LX,U      X5,SECTR          . SET POINTER TO CURRENT ITEM     @E@@@4SG
)@@G@@          LX,U      A3,WORK           . WORK AREA FOR FDSUBS@F@@@4      SH
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,FDABR         . FAKE AN ABSOLUTE READ     @F@@@4      SI
)@@G@@    LX        X11,GTSTRT        . RESTORE RETURN ADDRESS    @F@@@4      SJ
)@@G@@    JZ        A0,0,X11          . RETURN NOW IF STATUS OK   @D@@@4      SK
)@@G@@    LR        R1,A0             . SAVE STATUS   @E@@@4          P$RINT  SL
)@@G@@  A5                . PRINT THE MESSAGE   @E@@@4          LA        A0,RSM
)@@G@@1             . RESTIRE STATUS\     @C@@@4          J         0,X11     SN
)@@G@@        . TAKE IT @[@@@4.     @[@@@4.     @G@@@4. ROUTINE TO TEST USER ISO
)@@G@@DENTITY BEFORE DIVULGING SECURE INFORMATION     @F@@@4.    (REMOVABLE DISP
)@@G@@SK PACKIDS OR CATALOGUED TAPE FILE REEL NUMBERS)@[@@@4.     @H@@@4. FOR SQ
)@@G@@STUDENTS WHO ARE NOT ACCOUNT MANAGERS, THE REQUESTING ACCOUNT NUMBER    SR
)@@G@@@D@@@4.    AND THE ACCOUNT NUMBER OF THE FILE MUST MATCH.   @G@@@4. FOR SS
)@@G@@OTHERS, ONLY THE FIRST SIX CHARACTERS OF THE ACCOUNTS MUST MATCH. @[@@@4ST
)@@G@@.     @ @@@4. CALL:   LMJ    X11,SECURITY @ @@@4.         <RETURN TO TELSU
)@@G@@L ALL>@H@@@4.         <HEAR NO EVIL, SEE NO EVIL, BUT ABOVE ALL, SPEAK NSV
)@@G@@OTHING SECURE>    @[@@@4.     @C@@@4SECURITY                            SW

)@@G@@        . NOT NEEDED IF NOT AT UOM  @E@@@4          SX        X11,SECX11TC
)@@G@@        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @F@@@4          LMJ       X11,BADGUY      TD

)@@G@@  . HE ISN'T, RETURN WITH OUT A WRD @G@@@4          LA        A0,ACCOUNTTF

)@@G@@*   PROC                        .   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.         THIS PROEO
)@@G@@C DEFINES THE FIELDS IN MAIN, LEAD, AND SEARCH ITEMS FROM   @H@@@@.     EP
)@@G@@    AN EXEC-8 FILE DIRECTORY.  THE DEFINITIONS WERE EXTRACTED FROM THE  EQ
)@@G@@@I@@@@.         ELEMENT DRC IN LEVEL 26.70.117 OF EXEC-8.  THE CALL TO TER
)@@G@@HE PROC IS OF     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.         THIS HAS BEEN UPDATED TO IES
)@@G@@NCLUDE SOME OF THE LEVEL 33 DEFINITIONS   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@.         THET
)@@G@@E FORM:     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.                   DIPROC XM,XL,XS @[@@@@EU
)@@G@@.     @H@@@@.         WHERE XM, XL, AND XS ARE THE INDEX REGISTERS TO BEEV
)@@G@@ USED TO POINT TO @H@@@@.         THE MAIN, LEAD, AND SEARCH ITEMS RESPEEW
)@@G@@CTIVELY.  ANY OF THE THREE    @A@@@@.         SUB-FIELDS MAY BE ZERO.   EX
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@XM        EQU       DIPROC(1,1)       . INDEX REGISTEREY
)@@G@@ FOR MAIN ITEM    @G@@@@XL        EQU       DIPROC(1,2)       . INDEX REEZ
)@@G@@GISTER FOR LEAD ITEM    @G@@@@XS        EQU       DIPROC(1,3)       . INFA
)@@G@@DEX REGISTER FOR SEARCH ITEM  @ @@@@. * SEARCH ENTRY DEFINITIONS  @F@@@@FB
)@@G@@SQUAL*    $EQUF     1,XS              . SEARCH ENTRY QUALIFIER    @F@@@@FC
)@@G@@SFILE*    $EQUF     3,XS              . FILE WORD IN SEARCH ENTRY @G@@@@FD
)@@G@@SLITEM*   $EQUF     5,XS              . SEARCH ENTRY LEAD ITEM ADDRESS  FE
)@@G@@@F@@@@SCOUNT*   $EQUF     5,0,U             . $ SEARCH ITEM ENTRY COUNT FF
)@@G@@@ @@@@. * LEAD ITEM DEFINITIONS     @G@@@@LEAD*     EQU       0         FG
)@@G@@        . RELATIVE POSITION OF LEAD ITEM  @F@@@@LILINK*   $EQUF     LEADFH
)@@G@@,XL           . LINK ADDRESS IN LEAD ITEM @E@@@@LQUAL*    $EQUF     LEADFI
)@@G@@+1,XL         . LEAD ITEM QUALIFIER @E@@@@LFILE*    $EQUF     LEAD+3,XL FJ
)@@G@@        . LEAD ITEM FILE NAME @E@@@@LPROJ*    $EQUF     LEAD+5,XL       FK
)@@G@@  . PROJECT IN LEAD ITEM@F@@@@RDKEY*    $EQUF     LEAD+7,XL         . REFL
)@@G@@AD KEY IN LEAD ITEM     @F@@@@WRKEY*    $EQUF     LEAD+8,XL         . WRFM
)@@G@@ITE KEY IN LEAD ITEM    @E@@@@FTYPE*    $EQUF     LEAD+9,XL,S1      . MEFN
)@@G@@DIUM IN LEAD ITEM @F@@@@                                      . 0 - FIXEFO
)@@G@@D MASS STORAGE    @C@@@@                                      . 1 - TAPEFP

)@@G@@@F@@@@RCYCT*    $EQUF     LEAD+9,XL,S4      . CURRENT RANGE OF F-CYCLES FT
)@@G@@@G@@@@ACYC*     $EQUF     LEAD+9,XL,T3      . MOST CURRENT ABSOLUTE CYCLFU
)@@G@@E     @ @@@@. * MAIN ITEM DEFINITIONS     @G@@@@FILE*     EQU       0   FV

)@@G@@        . SET IF THIS IS A TAPE FILE@H@@@@REMF*     $EQUF     00010,,U  HZ
)@@G@@        . SET IF THIS FILE IS ON REMOVABLE DISC *[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@      IA
)@@G@@    AXR$,1  @#@@@@          IOPROC  @#@@@@$(1)      LIT     @[@@@@.     IB
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @C@@@@.         CALL MCTSCH (SCRTCH,STATUS,MCTBUF)    @[@@@@IC
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@.         THIS SUBROUTINE SEARCHES THE FILE NAMED IN THE FIRID
)@@G@@ST ARGUMENT @G@@@@.         FOR AN MCT.  THE FILE MUST NAVE BEEN CREATEDIE
)@@G@@ BY THE SUBROUTINE@G@@@@.         DMTAPE FROM A SECURE DIRECTORY TAPE.  IF
)@@G@@DMTAPE WILL LEAVE A COPY@G@@@@.         OF THE SYSTEM MCT IN THE FIRST TIG
)@@G@@RACK AFTER THE END OF THE     @G@@@@.         DIRECTORY COPY.  THE FIRSTIH
)@@G@@ ARGUMENT MUST BE THE ADDRESS OF A  @C@@@@.         BUFFER AT LEAST 28 WII
)@@G@@ORDS IN LENGTH.   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         THE SECOND ARGUMENT WILL BIJ
)@@G@@E ZERO IF THE MCT WAS FOUND, AND    @C@@@@.         EQUAL TO ONE IF IT WIK
)@@G@@AS NOT FOUND.     @[@@@@.     @G@]@@.         THE THIRD AGRUMENT MUST BEIL
)@@G@@ A BUFFER AT LEAST 1792 WORDS LONG  @H@@@].         THE THIRD AGRUMENT MIM
)@@G@@UST BE A BUFFER AT LEAST 'MCTSIZE' WORDS LONG   @E@@@@.         AND WILLIN
)@@G@@ CONTAIN THE MCT AS IT IS READ FROM THE   @ @@@@.         DIRECTORY FILEIO
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @I@@@]MCTSIZE   EQU       2*1792            . TWO TRKSIP
)@@G@@ GIVES US ALL WE NEED (FOR NOW)     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@MCTSCH*           IQ
)@@G@@                    . ENTRY   @H@@@@          SZ        A3              IR
)@@G@@  . FOR FORTRAN ADR=IND COMPATABILITY     @F@@@@          LX,U      A0,*IS
)@@G@@0,X11         . GET FILE NAME ADDRESS     @F@@@@          LR,U      R1,*IT
)@@G@@2,X11         . GET ADDRESS OF MCT BUFFER @G@@@@          LX,U      A2,0IU
)@@G@@,A0           . SAVE SCRATCH AREA BUFFER ADDRESS@G@@@@          LXI,U   IV
)@@G@@  A0,10             . FITEM$ PKT LENGTH FOR FASTRAND  @F@@@@          ERIW
)@@G@@        FITEM$            . FIND OUT ABOUT THE FILE   @E@@@@          SSIX
)@@G@@L       A0,30             . ISOLATE THE STATUS  @F@@@@          JNZ     IY
)@@G@@  A0,ERR            . ERR IF NOT FASTRAND FORMAT@F@@@@          TNZ     IZ
)@@G@@  2,A2              . WAS THE FILE @ASG'ED ?    @D@@@@          J       JA
)@@G@@  ERR               . NO, ERR STATUS@F@@@@          LA,H1     A4,9,A2   JB
)@@G@@        . GET THE LAST TRACK WRITTEN@D@@@@          LA        A1,(R$,0,0JC
)@@G@@)       . FUNCTION WORD @G@@@@          LX,U      A0,0,A2           . FIJD
)@@G@@TEM$ PKT WILL BE IOW$ PKT     @H@]@@          ANA,U     A4,1            JE
)@@G@@  . BACK UP TRACK WRITTEN FOR COMPARE     @F@@@@          LX        A2,RJF
)@@G@@1             . GET MCT BUFFER ADDRESS    @G@@@@          SA        A1,IJG
)@@G@@OSWRD         . SET THE STATUS/FUNCTION WORD    @E@@@@          LXI,U   JH
)@@G@@  A2,3              . WE WILL READ 3 WORDS@F@@@@          SZ        IODAJI
)@@G@@DD            . STARTING AT SECTOR ZERO   @E@@@@          SX        A2,IJJ
)@@G@@OACW          . SET THE ACCESS WORD @F@@@@          ER        IOW$      JK
)@@G@@        . READ THE DIRECTORY HEADER @E@@@@          TNZ       IOSTAT    JL
)@@G@@        . READ OK ? AND...    @G@@@@          TZ,H1     1,A2            JM
)@@G@@  . DOES THIS LOOK LIKE A DIRECTORY @F@@@@          J         ERR       JN
)@@G@@        . NO TO EITHER, ERR RETURN  @H@]@@          TNE,H2    A4,2,A2   JO
)@@G@@        . IS THERE AN EXTRA GRANULE FOR MCT ?   @G@@@]          TLE,H2  JP
)@@G@@  A4,2,A2           . ARE THERE EXTRA TRACKS FOR MCT ?@E@]@@          J JQ
)@@G@@        $+3               . YES, EXACTLY ONE    @G@]@@          TG,H2   JR
)@@G@@  A4,2,A2           . IS THERE MORE THAN ONE EXTRA ?  @D@@@@          J JS
)@@G@@        ERR               . NO, ERR RETURN@G@]@@          LA,U      A1,1JT
)@@G@@792           . READ A TRACK'S WORTH OF MCT     @H@@@]          LA,U    JU
)@@G@@  A1,MCTSIZE        . FILL THE PROVIDED BUFFER WITH MCT     @G@@@@      JV
)@@G@@    LA,H2     A4,2,A2           . DIR TRACK COUNT IS MCT ADDRESS  @G@@@@JW
)@@G@@          SA        A1,IOWRDS         . SET THE WORD COUNT ( 1 TRACK)   JX
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LSSL      A4,6              . CHANGE TRACKS INTO SECTORSJY
)@@G@@@E@@@@          SA        A4,IODADD         . AND THE DRUM ADDRESS@D@@@@JZ
)@@G@@          ER        IOW$              . READ THE MCT  @E@[@@          LAKA
)@@G@@        A4,('SYMMCT')     . IDENTIFIES THE MCT  @E@[@@          TNZ     KB
)@@G@@  IOSTAT            . DID WE READ IT OK ? @E@]@[          TZ        IOSTKC
)@@G@@AT            . DID WE READ IT OK ? @E@@@]          TNZ       IOSTAT    KD
)@@G@@        . DID WE READ IT OK ? @C@@@]          J         READOK          KE
)@@G@@  . YES     @E@@@]          L         A1,IOSTAT         . NO, CHECK STATKF
)@@G@@US    @F@@@]          TE,U      A1,5              . STATUS 5 MEANS TRUNCKG
)@@G@@ATED  @E@[@@          TE        A4,0,A2           . AND IS THIS AN MCT ?KH
)@@G@@@D@@@@          J         ERR               . NO, ERR RETURN@E@]@[      KI
)@@G@@    LA        A4,('SYMMCT')     . IDENTIFIES THE MCT  @F@]@[          LAKJ
)@@G@@,U      A1,'MCT'          . LOAD H2 OF L36 MCT ID'S   @D@@@]READOK    LAKK
)@@G@@,U      A1,'MCT'          . MCT IDENTIFIER@F@]@[          TNE       A4,0KL
)@@G@@,A2           . IS IT A L33 OR LESS MCT   @E@]@[          J         GOODKM
)@@G@@              . YES I'T A VALID MCT @F@]@[          TE,H2     A1,0,A2   KN
)@@G@@        . IS IT AN L36 OR UP MCT    @F@@@]          TE,H1     A1,0,A2   KO
)@@G@@        . IS IT AN L36 OR UP MCT    @H@]@[          J         ERR       KP
)@@G@@        . NOT A VALID MCT BY ANY EXEC LEVEL     @E@@@]          J       KQ
)@@G@@  ERR               . NOT A VALID MCT     @[@@@].     @F@@@].         WEKR
)@@G@@ NOW HAVE THE PARTS OF THE MCT WHICH WERE SAVED BY    @^@@@].         SEKS
)@@G@@CURE OR FAS.@G@@@].         SECURE SAVES 11 WORDS OF THE POINTER TABLE, KT
)@@G@@THE SYSTEM ID     @F@@@].         TABLE, AND THE I/O SECTION.  THERE IS KU
)@@G@@NO FIXPAX TABLE   @G@@@].         FAS SAVES THE POINTER TABLE, THE SYSTEKV
)@@G@@M ID TABLE, AND THE     @F@@@].         FIXPAX TABLE.  WE NEED TO ADJUSTKW
)@@G@@ POINTERS SO FIXPAX CAN @^@@@].         BE FOUND.     @[@@@].     @F@@@]KX
)@@G@@          TZ,S1     13,A2             . IS POINTER TABLE TRUNCATED@F@@@]KY
)@@G@@          J         SECFMT            . YES, SECURE FORMAT TAPE   @F@@@]KZ
)@@G@@.                                     . NO, MUST BE FAS FORMAT    @F@@@]LA
)@@G@@          L,H2      A1,1,A2           . START OF SYSTEM-ID AREA   @F@@@]LB
)@@G@@          A,H1      A1,1,A2           . LENGTH OF SYSTEM-ID AREA  @F@@@]LC
)@@G@@          S,H2      A1,7,A2           . START OF FIXPAX TABLE     @E@@@]LD
)@@G@@                                      . THAT'S ALL FAS SAVES@F@]@[GOOD  LE
)@@G@@                                . RETRUN WITH NO ERRORS     @F@@@]GOOD  LF
)@@G@@                                . RETURN WITH NO ERRORS     @F@@@@      LG
)@@G@@    SZ        *1,X11            . CLEAR THE STATUS WORD     @C@@@@      LH
)@@G@@    J         4,X11             . RETURN  @G@@@@ERR       SR        R1,*LI
)@@G@@1,X11         . SET IT FOR UNSUCCESSFUL RETURN  @C@@@@          J       LJ
)@@G@@  4,X11             . GO BACK @[@@@].     @F@@@].         SECURE FORMAT,LK
)@@G@@ WE NEED TO BUILD A FAKE FIXPAX TABLE     @[@@@].     @F@@@]SECFMT    L,LL
)@@G@@U       A0,11             . SIZE OF SECURE'S PTR TABLE@F@@@^          S,LM
)@@G@@H2      A0,1,A2           . SET PTR TO SYSTEM-ID TBL  @F@@@]          A,LN
)@@G@@H1      A0,1,A2           . SIZE OF SYSTEM-ID AREA    @E@@@]          A,LO
)@@G@@H1      A0,3,A2           . SIZE OF I/O SECTION @G@@@]          S,H2    LP
)@@G@@  A0,7,A2           . PUT FAKE FIXPAX TABLE THERE     @E@@@]          AULQ
)@@G@@,H1     A0,7,A2           . END OF FIXPAX TABLE @H@#@]          TG,U    LR
)@@G@@  A1,MCTSIZ+1       . MAKE SURE WE DON'T OVERFLOW TABLE     @H@@@#      LS
)@@G@@    TG,U      A1,MCTSIZE+1      . MAKE SURE WE DON'T OVERFLOW TABLE     LT
)@@G@@@E@@@]          J         ERR               . NOT ENOUGH ROOM     @E@@@]LU
)@@G@@          A,U       A0,,A2            . POINT TO BEGINNING  @^@@@]      LV
)@@G@@    LXI,U     A0,1@E@@@]          L,H1      A1,7,A2           . LENGTH OLW
)@@G@@F TABLE     @G@@@]          AN,U      A1,1              . MINUS 1 => NUMLX

)@@G@@@F@@@]          JGD       A1,$+1            . DECREMENT BY 1 FOR JGD    LZ

)@@G@@@ @@@]          JGD       A1,$-1    @C@@@]          J         GOOD      MB
)@@G@@        . ALL DONE@#@@@@          END     _@@@@@  A4,0,A1           . MCMC
)@@G@@T IDENTIFIER@G@@@]          LA,H1     A0,7,A1           . GET LENGTH OF MD
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@A@@@@      SUBROUTINE DTRKS(FDBUFF,WORK) @[@@@@C     @F@@@@ME
)@@G@@C     THIS SUBROUTINE PRINTS THE NUMBER OF DIRECTORY TRACKS WHICH @G@@@@MF
)@@G@@C     ARE ON EACH UNIT.  FDBUFF IS AN ARRAY INITIALIZED BY SUBROUTINE   MG
)@@G@@@D@@@@C     FDI.  WORK IS A WORK ARRAY DIMENSIONED AT 32.   @[@@@@C     MH
)@@G@@@ @@@@      IMPLICIT INTEGER(A-Z)   @A@@@@      DIMENSION FDBUFF(56),WORMI
)@@G@@K(32) @^@@@@      PARAMETER ENTSIZ=5@E@@@@      TOTAL=FLD(18,18,FDBUFF(1MJ
)@@G@@3))-FLD(0,18,FDBUFF(13))+1    @A@@@@      CALL EOPEN(WORK,22,WORK(11))  MK
)@@G@@@D@@@@      CALL EMSG(WORK,'DIRECTORY TRACKS:  TOTAL-&')    @ @@@@      ML
)@@G@@CALL EDECV(WORK,TOTAL)  @E@]@@      IF (FDBUFF(14).LT.0) GO TO 50  @ THIMM
)@@G@@S IS POST LEVEL 32@#@]@@      TALLY=0     @A@]@@      J=FDBUFF(9)-LOC(FDMN
)@@G@@BUFF(1))+4  @A@]@@      SSUNIT=FLD(0,18,FDBUFF(J))    @^@]@@      DO 40 MO
)@@G@@I=1,TOTAL   @#@]@@      J=J+ENTSIZ  @^@]@@      TALLY=TALLY+1     @ @]@@MP
)@@G@@      IF(I.EQ.TOTAL) GO TO 10 @A@]@@      NEWSSU=FLD(0,18,FDBUFF(J))    MQ
)@@G@@@A@]@@      IF(SSUNIT.EQ.NEWSSU) GO TO 40 @^@]@@10    CALL ESKIP(WORK,2)MR
)@@G@@@B@]@@      CALL EDECV(WORK,FLD(18,12,SSUNIT))  @ @]@@      CALL ECHAR(WMS
)@@G@@ORK,'/')    @B@]@@      CALL EDECV(WORK,FLD(30,6,SSUNIT))   @ @]@@      MT
)@@G@@CALL ECHAR(WORK,'-')    @ @]@@      CALL EDECV(WORK,TALLY)  @^@]@@      MU
)@@G@@SSUNIT=NEWSSU     @#@]@@      TALLY=0     @ @]@@      IF(I.EQ.TOTAL) GO MV
)@@G@@TO 20 @ @]@@      CALL ECOLN(WORK,COLN)   @ @]@@      IF(COLN.LT.120) GOMW

)@@G@@,WORK(11))  @^@]@@      CALL ECOL(WORK,17)@#@]@@40    CONTINUE    @]@]@@MY

)@@G@@))-1  @A@@@@C     RETRIEVE THE FIXPAX TABLE     @A@@@@      CALL GTFPAX NA
)@@G@@(WORK(33),UNITS)  @A@@@@      J=FDBUFF(9)-LOC(FDBUFF(1))-1  @#@@@@60    NB
)@@G@@CONTINUE    @E@@@@      IF (FLD(0,12,FDBUFF(J)).EQ.1) GO TO 70 @ SKIP UNNC
)@@G@@IT 0  @]@@@@      J=J+1 @#@@@@      GO TO 60    @#@@@@70    CONTINUE    ND
)@@G@@@^@@@@      DO 140 I=1,UNITS  @]@@@@      SUM=0 @#@@@@80    CONTINUE    NE
)@@G@@@C@@@@      IF (FLD(18,18,FDBUFF(J)).EQ.0) GO TO 110  @G@@@@      K=3+FLNF
)@@G@@D(18,18,FDBUFF(J))-LOC(FDBUFF(1)) @ POINT AT 2ND TRACK ENTRY@]@@@@      NG
)@@G@@L=K   @#@@@@90    CONTINUE    @G@@@@      IF (AND(FDBUFF(K+1),255).EQ.0)NH
)@@G@@ GO TO 100 @ WE HAVE ALL TRACKS     @]@@@@      K=K+2 @#@@@@      GO TO NI
)@@G@@90    @#@@@@100   CONTINUE    @ @@@@      SUM=SUM+((K-L)/2)+1     @#@@@@NJ
)@@G@@110   CONTINUE    @]@@@@      J=J+1 @G@@@@      IF (FLD(0,12,FDBUFF(J)).NK
)@@G@@EQ.I) GO TO 80 @ GET ALL FOR THIS UNIT    @ @@@@      IF (SUM.EQ.0) GO TNL
)@@G@@O 120 @ @@@@      CALL ESKIP (WORK,2)     @#@@@@      K=WORK(32+I)@ @@@#NM
)@@G@@      IF (K.NE.0) GO TO 115   @A@@@#      CALL EFD1 (WORK, 'LDAT  ')    NN
)@@G@@@ @@@#      CALL EOCTF (WORK,3,I)   @#@@@#      GO TO 116   @B@]@@      NO

)@@G@@@ @#@@      CALL ECHAR (WORK,'-')   @ @@@#116   CALL ECHAR (WORK,'-')   NT
)@@G@@@ @@@@      CALL EDECV (WORK,SUM)   @#@@@@120   CONTINUE    @A@@@@      NU
)@@G@@IF (I.EQ.UNITS) GO TO 130     @ @@@@      CALL ECOLN (WORK,COLN)  @A@@@@NV

)@@G@@@]@@@@      END   _@@@@@I-*G*)I[>H90H->^K,^@)E-*HD3^[-IL(IT4H9<IL-GT9^[(NZ
)@@G@@IS)^L7HD4H[\I(4^[2GD,HS)H92^[4HD4H->BS)IL>G9-IL=H->IT3@M@@@@H9&^[*H9,H92OA
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@[          AXR$,1  @[@@@[$(1)  @[@@@[.     @F@@@[.     OB
)@@G@@    THIS ELEMENT CONTAINS TWO FORTRAN CALLABLE SUBROUTINES  @F@@@[.     OC
)@@G@@    WHICH SAVE (SVFPAX) AND GET (GTFPAX) THE FIXPAX TABLE   @F@@@[.     OD
)@@G@@    FOUND IN POST LEVEL 32 MASTER CONFIGURATION TABLES.     @[@@@[.     OE
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @]@@@[.  SVFPAX   @F@@@[.         SAVE THE FIXPAX TABLE IN AOF
)@@G@@ CORE AREA REQUESTED FROM THE @G@@@[.         MCORE SUBROUTINE AND SAVE OG
)@@G@@THE ADDRESS OF THAT AREA IN THE     @ @@@[.         LOCAL CELL FIXPAX.  OH
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @C@@@[.         CALL:       CALL SVFPAX(MCTADD,UNITS) @F@@@[OI
)@@G@@.                     MCTADD IS THE ADDRESS OF A COPY OF THE MCT  @F@@@[OJ
)@@G@@.                     UNITS  IS A COUNT OF THE MASS STORAGE UNITS @[@@@[OK
)@@G@@.     @[@@@[.     @B@@@[SVFPAX*                               .   @E@@@[OL
)@@G@@          SZ        A3                . FOR FORTRAN CALLING @F@]@[      OM
)@@G@@    LX,U      A0,*0,X11         . ADDRESS OF THE MCT COPY   @F@@@]      ON
)@@G@@    LX,U      A1,*0,X11         . ADDRESS OF THE MCT COPY   @D@]@[      OO
)@@G@@    LA,H1     A4,0,A0           . MCT IDENTIFIER@D@^@]          LA,H1   OP
)@@G@@  A4,0,A1           . MCT IDENTIFIER@G@@@]          LA,H1     A0,7,A1   OQ
)@@G@@        . GET LENGTH OF L35 MASS STORE IDS@H@]@[          LA,H2     A5,7OR
)@@G@@,A0           . POINTER TO LEVEL 35 MASS STORE IDS    @H@@@]          LAOS
)@@G@@,H2     A5,7,A1           . POINTER TO LEVEL 35 MASS STORE IDS    @I@]@[OT
)@@G@@          AA,U      A5,1,A0           . CHANGE FROM MCT RELATIVE TO PROGOU
)@@G@@RAM ABS     @I@@@]          AA,U      A5,1,A1           . CHANGE FROM MCOV
)@@G@@T RELATIVE TO PROGRAM ABS     @F@^@[          TNE,U     A4,'MCT'        OW
)@@G@@  . IS THIS LEVEL 35 OR HIGHER@G@^@[          J         GETSPC          OX
)@@G@@  . YES, NO NEED TO SEARCH FOR TABLE@F@]@[          LA,T2     A4,5,A0   OY

)@@G@@        . SYSTEM LEVEL INDICATOR    @G@^@[          TLE,U     A4,4      PA
)@@G@@        . IS THIS LEVEL 33 OR GREATER ?   @G@^@[          J         3,X1PB
)@@G@@1             . NO, RETURN WITH NO ACTION TAKEN @G@]@[          LA      PC
)@@G@@  A4,026,A0         . POINTER WORD TO DN MEM LIST     @G@^@]          LAPD
)@@G@@        A4,026,A1         . POINTER WORD TO DN MEM LIST     @G@^@[      PE
)@@G@@    AND,U     A4,0777           . ISOLATE THE POINTER OF INTEREST @H@^@[PF
)@@G@@          TNZ       A5                . IS DN MEMORY CAPABILITY CONFIGURPG
)@@G@@ED ?  @H@]@[          LA,H2     A5,030,A0         . NO, GET POINTER TO EPH
)@@G@@QUIP MNEMONICS    @H@^@]          LA,H2     A5,030,A1         . NO, GET PI
)@@G@@POINTER TO EQUIP MNEMONICS    @F@^@[          ANA       A5,*1,X11       PJ
)@@G@@  . BACK UP TO FIXPAX START   @F@]@[          AA,U      A5,0,A0         PK

)@@G@@  . ADD START OF MCT ADDRESS  @G@]@[          LA        A0,*1,X11       PM
)@@G@@  . FIXPAX TABLE LENGTH = UNIT COUNT@G@^@]          LA        A0,*1,X11 PN
)@@G@@        . FIXPAX TABLE LENGTH = UNIT COUNT@F@^@[GETSPC    SX        X11,PO
)@@G@@A4            . SAVE THE RETURN ADDRESS   @F@@@^          SX        X11,PP
)@@G@@A4            . SAVE THE RETURN ADDRESS   @F[@@[          LMJ       X11,PQ
)@@G@@MCORE         . GET SPACE TO THE TABLE_   @D@@@[          LX        X11,PR
)@@G@@A4            . RESTORE RETURN@G@@@[          LX        A1,A5           PS
)@@G@@  . GET MCT LOC OF FIXPAX TABLE     @F@@@[          LXI,U     A0,1      PT
)@@G@@        . SET INC FOR BLOCK TRANSFER@F@@@[          LR        R1,*1,X11 PU
)@@G@@        . NUMBER OF WORDS TO MOVE   @F@@@[          SX        A0,FIXPAX PV
)@@G@@        . SAVE THE FIXPAX TABLE LOC @E@@@[          LXI,U     A1,1      PW
)@@G@@        . ANOTHER INCREMENT   @H@@@[          BT        A0,0,*A1        PX
)@@G@@  . MOVE THE FIXPAX TABLE INTO MEMORY     @E@^@[          SX        X1,SPY
)@@G@@VX1           . SACRED REGISTER     @D@^@[          LX,U      A0,*0,X11 PZ
)@@G@@        . MCT ADDRESS   @E@^@[          LA,H1     A2,0,A0           . GEQA
)@@G@@T MCT IDENTIFIER  @D@^@[          TNE,U     A2,'MCT'          . LEVEL 35QB
)@@G@@ ?    @D@@@[          J         3,X11             . YES, ALL DONE @D@^@[QC
)@@G@@          LA        A5,*1,X11         . UNIT COUNT    @F@^@[          LXQD
)@@G@@        X1,FIXPAX         . POINT AT FIXPAX TABLE COPY@F@^@[          LXQE
)@@G@@        A2,A0             . SAVE MCT BASE ADDRESS     @H@^@[          AXQF
)@@G@@,H2     A2,027,A0         . COMPUTE ADDR OF SPECIFIC EQUIP TAB    @G@^@[QG
)@@G@@          AA,U      A5,0,X1           . COMPUTE ADDR OF LAST TAB ENTRY  QH
)@@G@@@G@^@[          ANX,U     A2,1              . SUB FOR GOOD INDEX INTO TAQI
)@@G@@BLE   @F@^@[NXTENT    TZ        0,X1              . IS THIS A VOID ENTRYQJ
)@@G@@ ?    @G@^@[          TZ,H2     0,X1              . OR IS THIS A PACKID QK
)@@G@@ENTRY ?     @H@^@[          J         NOTSSU            . YES TO EITHER,QL
)@@G@@ GET THE NEXT ENTRY     @F@^@[          AU,T2     A0,6,A0           . POQM
)@@G@@INT AT SS INDEX TABLE   @F@^@[          AX,T1     A1,0,X1           . GEQN
)@@G@@T SS ENTRY FOR THIS LDAT@H@^@[          AU,T3     A0,0,A1           . GEQO

)@@G@@        . GET ADDR OF EQUIP MNEMONIC@E@^@[          LA        A4,0,A3   QQ
)@@G@@        . GET EQUIP MNEMONIC  @E@^@[          LX        A3,(1,-1)       QR
)@@G@@  . FOR TABLE SEARCH    @G@^@[          LR,U      R1,EQMNL          . LEQS
)@@G@@NGTH OF MNEMONIC-SHIFT TABLE  @G@^@[          SE        A4,EQSTAB+1,*A3 QT
)@@G@@  . LOOK FOR THIS EQUIP MNEMONIC    @D@^@[          J         NOEQP     QU
)@@G@@        . NOT FOUND     @G@^@[          LX        A3,SHIFT,A3       . GEQV
)@@G@@T SHIFT COUNT FOR THIS EQUIP  @E@^@[          LA,S3     A4,0,X1         QW
)@@G@@  . GET UNIT DESIGNATOR @G@^@[          SSL       A4,0,A3           . MAQX
)@@G@@KE THE UNIT LOOK LIKE A UNIT  @F@^@[          SA,S3     A4,0,X1         QY
)@@G@@  . RESTORE TO FIXPAX TABLE   @H@^@[NOTSSU    TLEM      X1,A5           QZ
)@@G@@  . BUMP POINTER AND TEST FOR TAB END     @H@^@[          J         NXTERA
)@@G@@NT            . PROCESS NEXT ENTRY IN FIXPAX TABLE    @C@^@[          LXRB
)@@G@@        X1,SVX1           . RESTORE @C@^@[          J         3,X11     RC
)@@G@@        . RETURN  @E@^@[NOEQP     SA        A4,MSG+2          . UNFOUNDERD
)@@G@@D EQUIP CODE@G@^@[          SA        A0,A3             . SAVE A0 FROM PRE
)@@G@@RINT$ AND CSF$    @G@^@[          P$RINT    MSGP              . TELL THERF
)@@G@@ USER ABOUT THE PROBLEM @F@^@[          LX,U      A0,LOGIMG         . PURG
)@@G@@T IT IN THE LOG ALSO    @F@^@[          ER        CSF$              . HORH
)@@G@@PEFULLY, IT WILL BE SEEN@E@^@[          LA        A0,A3             . RERI
)@@G@@STORE MCT ADDRESS @F@^@[          J         NOTSSU            . LOOK AT RJ
)@@G@@THE NEXT UNIT     @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @]@@@[.   GTFPAX  RK
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @E@@@[.         THIS ROUTINE RETRIVES THE FIXPAX TABLE FROM RL
)@@G@@ITS   @F@@@[.         SAVED LOCATION, TRANSFERING IT TO THE MEMORY ADDRERM
)@@G@@SS    @F@@@[.         PASSED AS THE FIRST ARGUMENT IN THE FORTRAN CALLINRN
)@@G@@G     @#@@@[.         SEQENCE.@[@@@[.     @C@@@[.         CALL:    CALL RO
)@@G@@GTFPAX (FIXPAX,UNITS)   @[@@@[.     @H@@@[.                  FIXPAX IS TRP
)@@G@@HE ARRAY TO BE FILLED WITH THE FIXPAX TABLE     @F@@@[.                 RQ
)@@G@@ UNITS  IS THE NUMBER OF UNITS (LENGTH OF TABLE)@[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     RR
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @C@@@[GTFPAX*                               . ENTRY   @F@@@[RS
)@@G@@          SZ        A3                . FOR FORTRAN COMPATABILITY @E@@@[RT
)@@G@@          LX,U      A1,*0,X11         . DESTINATION ADDRESS @F@@@[      RU
)@@G@@    LX        A0,FIXPAX         . LOCATION OF SAVED COPY    @F@@@[      RV
)@@G@@    LXI,U     A1,1              . INCREMENT FOR TRANSFER    @D@@@[      RW
)@@G@@    LR        R1,*1,X11         . UNIT COUNT    @E@@@[          BT      RX
)@@G@@  A1,0,*A0          . TRANSFER THE COPY   @C@@@[          J         3,X1RY
)@@G@@1             . RETURN  @[@@@[$(2)  @G@@@[FIXPAX    RES       1         RZ
)@@G@@        . LOCATION OF SAVED FIXPAX TABLE  @G@^@[SVX1      RES       1   SA
)@@G@@              . SAVE X1 DURING SVFPAX ROUTINE   @H@^@[EQSTAB            SB
)@@G@@  . TABLE USED TO CONVERT EQUIP MNEMONICS TO SHIFT CONST    @#@^@[      SC
)@@G@@    'F2    '@#@^@[          'F3    '@#@^@[          'F8460 '@#@^@[      SD
)@@G@@    'C7013 '@#@^@[          'B7013 '@#@^@[          'FH432 '@#@^@[      SE
)@@G@@    'FH880 '@#@^@[          'FH1782'@#@^@[          'D8405 '@#@^@[      SF
)@@G@@    'D8414 '@#@^@[          'D8424 '@#@^@[          'D8425 '@#@^@[      SG
)@@G@@    'D8440 '@#@^@[          'D8430 '@#@^@[          'D8433 '@D@^@[EQMNL SH
)@@G@@    EQU       $-EQSTAB          . TABLE LENGTH  @G@^@[SHIFT             SI
)@@G@@                    . PROVIDES THE SHIFT CONSTANTS    @^@^@[          + SJ
)@@G@@        2   @^@^@[          +         3   @^@^@[          +         3   SK
)@@G@@@^@^@[          +         0   @^@^@[          +         0   @^@^@[      SL
)@@G@@    +         0   @^@^@[          +         0   @^@^@[          +       SM
)@@G@@  3   @^@^@[          +         2   @^@^@[          +         2   @^@^@[SN
)@@G@@          +         2   @^@^@[          +         2   @^@^@[          + SO
)@@G@@        2   @^@^@[          +         2   @^@^@[          +         2   SP
)@@G@@@E@^@[          DO 1-($-SHIFT=EQMNL) , +09 . E FLAG IF BAD LENGTH @[@^@[SQ

)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         EXIT:     A0 - STATUS     @D@@@@.           YX
)@@G@@        A1 - ADDRESS OF TRACK DESCRIPTOR  @C@@@@.                   A2 -YY
)@@G@@ CORE ADDRESS OF SECTOR @D@@@@.                   A3 - ADDRESS OF FDSUBSYZ
)@@G@@ BUFFER     @G@@@@.                   A4 - ABSOLUTE ADDRESS OF SECTOR INZA
)@@G@@ FILE DIRECTORY   @G@@@@.                   A5 - PRINT CONTROL WORD CORRZB
)@@G@@ESPONDING TO STATUS     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.    .    .    .  ZC
)@@G@@  .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .  @[@@@@.     ZD
)@@G@@@A@@@@.         CALL:     LMJ  X11,FDABR  @[@@@@.     @I@@@@.         ENZE
)@@G@@TRY:    A3 - ADDRESS OF FDSUBS BUFFER INITIALIZED BY FDINIT, FDRDAS     ZF
)@@G@@@F@@@@.                   A4 - ABSOLUTE ADDRESS OF DIRECTORY SECTOR     ZG
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         EXIT:     A0 - STATUS     @D@@@@.           ZH
