)@@G@@ ADDRESS OF SECTOR@D@@@@.                   A3 - ADDRESS OF FDSUBS BUFFEZJ
)@@G@@R     @G@@@@.                   A5 - PRINT CONTROL WORD CORRESPONDING TOZK
)@@G@@ STATUS     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    . ZL
)@@G@@   .    .    .    .    .    .    .  @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         CALL:   ZM
)@@G@@  LMJ  X11,FDLUT  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         ENTRY:    A0,A1 - QUALIFIEZN
)@@G@@R     @I@@@@.                   A3 - ADDRESS OF FDSUBS BUFFER INITIALIZEZO
)@@G@@D BY FDINIT, FDRDAS     @B@@@@.                   A4,A5 - FILE NAME     ZP
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         EXIT:     A0 - STATUS     @A@@@@.           ZQ
)@@G@@        A4 - LUT ENTRY  @G@@@@.                   A5 - PRINT CONTROL WORZR
)@@G@@D CORRESPONDING TO STATUS     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.    .    .    .    .   ZS
)@@G@@ .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .  @[@@@@.     @A@@@@ZT
)@@G@@.         CALL:     LMJ  X11,FDHASH @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         ENTRY:  ZU
)@@G@@  A0,A1 - QUALIFIER     @I@@@@.                   A3 - ADDRESS OF FDSUBSZV
)@@G@@ BUFFER INITIALIZED BY FDINIT, FDRDAS     @B@@@@.                   A4,AZW
)@@G@@5 - FILE NAME     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         EXIT:     A0 - STATUS     ZX
)@@G@@@A@@@@.                   A1 - HASH INDEX @G@@@@.                   A5 -ZY
)@@G@@ PRINT CONTROL WORD CORRESPONDING TO STATUS     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. THE ZZ
)@@G@@STATUS CODES RETURNED IN A0 INDICATE THE FOLLOWING    @[@@@@.     @C@@@@AA
)@@G@@.          0      REQUEST COMPLETED NORMALLY    @E@@@@.          1      AB
)@@G@@ALL SECTORS HAVE BEEN RETURNED BY FDNDI   @F@@@@.          2      FDINITAC
)@@G@@ I/O ERROR READING FIRST 3 WORDS OF FILE  @G@@@@.          3      FDINITAD
)@@G@@ I/O ERROR READING A DIRECTORY ALLOCATION SECTOR@F@@@@.          4      AE
)@@G@@MORE DIRECTORY TRACKS THAN ROUTINE CAN HANDLE. ;@F@@@@.                 AF
)@@G@@   REASSEMBLE ROUTINE WITH MAXTRK SET HIGHER.   @B@@@@.          5      AG
)@@G@@ERROR OBTAINING MCT     @E@@@@.          6      ERROR CALCULATING UNIT OAH
)@@G@@R EQUIPMENT TYPE  @E@@@@.          7      FDNDI I/O ERROR READING A DIREAI
)@@G@@CTORY TRACK @F@@@@.          8      SECTOR ON DIRECTORY TRACK, BUT NOT AAJ
)@@G@@LLOCATED    @F@@@@.          9      ADDRESS IS ON WAD UNIT, BUT NOT A SEAK
)@@G@@CTOR BOUNDRY@E@@@@.          10     FDABR ADDRESS IS NOT ON DIRECTORY TRAL
)@@G@@ACK   @C@@@@.          11     FDABR I/O ERROR READING SECTOR@D@@@@.     AM
)@@G@@     12     I/O ERROR READING LOOK-UP TABLE     @D@@@@.          13     AN
)@@G@@FUNCTION NOT ALLOWED FOR SDGET$ FILE@E@@@@.          14     DIRECTORY FIAO
)@@G@@LE NOT PROPERLY FORMATTED     @G@@@@.          15     MASTER CONFIGURATIAP
)@@G@@ON TABLE NOT PROPERLY FORMATTED     @[@@@@/.    @E@@@@          AXR$    AQ
)@@G@@                    . DEFINE REGISTERS    @D@@@@.         IOPROC* DEFINEAR
)@@G@@S THE FIELDS IN IN I/O PACKET @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THESE PROCS PROVIDE ANAS
)@@G@@ EASY WAY OF RESERVING SPACE IN ROUTINES  @ @@@@. WHICH HAVE A DYNAMIC DAT
)@@G@@BANK. @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC                        .   @B@@@@AU
)@@G@@BASE*     NAME                        .   @F@@@@LC*(1)    EQU       P(1,AV
)@@G@@1)            . SET BASE LOCATION COUNTER @E@@@@LC*(2)    EQU       P(1,AW
)@@G@@2)            . SET BASE REGISTER   @B@@@@          END                 AX
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC      *1                .   AY
)@@G@@@B@@@@REZ*      NAME                        .   @G@@@@*         EQUF    AZ
)@@G@@  LC(1),LC(2)       . DEF LABEL, BUT EQUF WON'T PRINT @F@@@@LC*(1)    EQBA
)@@G@@U       LC(1)+P(1,1)      . BUMP THE LOCATION COUNTER @B@@@@          ENBB
)@@G@@D                         .   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@IONAME    EQUF      0,A0BC
)@@G@@              . FILE NAME     @H@@@@IOSWRD    EQUF      3,A0            BD
)@@G@@  . WORD CONTAINING STATUS, FUNCTION, ETC.@C@@@@IOSTAT    EQUF      3,A0BE
)@@G@@,S1           . STATUS  @C@@@@IOFUNC    EQUF      3,A0,S2           . FUBF
)@@G@@NCTION@E@@@@IOAFC     EQUF      3,A0,S3           . ABNORMAL FRAME COUNTBG
)@@G@@@G@@@@IOSUB     EQUF      3,A0,H2           . SUBSTATUS (WORDS TRANSFERRBH
)@@G@@ED)   @D@@@@IOACW     EQUF      4,A0              . ACCESS WORD   @E@@@@BI
)@@G@@IOWRDS    EQUF      4,A0,H1           . WORDS TO TRANSFER   @D@@@@IOCADDBJ
)@@G@@    EQUF      4,A0,H2           . CORE ADDRESS  @D@@@@IODADD    EQUF    BK
)@@G@@  5,A0              . DRUM ADDRESS  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     BL
)@@G@@@G@@@@MAXTRK    EQU       16*256            . MAXIMUM DT'S TO PROCESS PEBM
)@@G@@R UNIT@F@@@@ENTSIZ    EQUF      2,,U              . SIZE OF DT DESCRIPTOBN
)@@G@@R     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          BASE      0,A3              . SET DBANBO
)@@G@@K START     @F@@@@L(0)      REZ       6                 . GET SPACE FOR BP
)@@G@@I/O PACKET  @D@@@@DLPKT     EQUF      L(0)              . I/O PACKET    BQ
)@@G@@@B@@@@L(0)      REZ       1                 .   @F@@@@TBFADD    EQUF    BR
)@@G@@  L(0)              . ADDRESS OF TRACK BUFFER   @B@@@@L(0)      REZ     BS
)@@G@@  1                 .   @D@@@@MCTADD    EQUF      L(0)              . ADBT
)@@G@@DRESS OF MCT@B@@@@L(0)      REZ       1                 .   @H@@@@DTIADDBU
)@@G@@    EQUF      L(0)              . DIRECTORY TRACK ITEM BUFFER ADDRESS   BV
)@@G@@@B@@@@L(0)      REZ       1                 .   @H@@@@DTISIZ    EQUF    BW
)@@G@@  L(0)              . SIZE OF DIRECTORY TRACK ITEM BUFFER   @G@@@@L(0)  BX
)@@G@@    REZ       4                 . 4 WORDS FOR FIRST 4 DGET$ WRDS  @F@@@@BY
)@@G@@TIMDAT    EQUF      L(0)              . TIME AND DATE OF CREATION @F@@@@BZ
)@@G@@CHECK     EQUF      TIMDAT+1,,H1      . MUST BE 0 FOR DIRECTORIES @F@@@@CA
)@@G@@LUTLEN    EQUF      TIMDAT+1,,H2      . LENGTH OF LOOK-UP TABLE   @F@@@@CB
)@@G@@DT1       EQUF      TIMDAT+2,,H1      . TRACK NUMBER OF FIRST DT  @H@@@@CC
)@@G@@DLSIZE    EQUF      TIMDAT+2,,H2      . NUMBER OF TRACKS WRITTEN BY DGETCD
)@@G@@$     @G@@@@L3332     EQUF      TIMDAT+3,,T1      . LEV 32/33 FLAG, SET CE
)@@G@@BY DGET$    @F@@@@STUNIT    EQUF      TIMDAT+3,,S2      . FLAG A NEW UNICF
)@@G@@T START     @B@@@@L(0)      REZ       1                 .   @F@@@@DLTRKSCG
)@@G@@    EQUF      L(0),,H1          . NUMBER OF DT'S PROCESSED  @F@@@@DT1ADDCH
)@@G@@    EQUF      L(0),,H2          . FILE ADDRESS OF FIRST DT  @B@@@@L(0)  CI
)@@G@@    REZ       1                 .   @G@@@@SINDEX    EQUF      L(0),,H1  CJ
)@@G@@        . SECTOR INDEX FOR DIRECTORY ITEM @G@@@@TINDEX    EQUF      L(0)CK
)@@G@@,,H2          . TRACK INDEX FOR DIRECTORY ITEM  @G@@@@ITEMNO    EQUF    CL
)@@G@@  TINDEX            . SEQ ITEM NUMBER FRO SDGET$  FILE@B@@@@L(0)      RECM
)@@G@@Z       2                 .   @F@@@@CBITS     EQUF      L(0)            CN
)@@G@@  . BIT MAP FOR CURRENT DT    @B@@@@L(0)      REZ       1               CO
)@@G@@  .   @G@@@@UNITS     EQUF      L(0),,T1          . UNIT COUNT FOR THIS CP
)@@G@@DIRECTORY   @F@@@@UTADD     EQUF      L(0),,H2          . CURRENT UNIT TCQ
)@@G@@AB POINTER  @B@@@@L(0)      REZ       1                 .   @H@@@@TRKADDCR
)@@G@@    EQUF      L(0),,H1          . FILE ADDRESS OF TRACK IN TRACK BUFFER CS
)@@G@@@F@@@@DTLADD    EQUF      L(0),,H2          . FILE ADDRESS OF LAST DT   CT
)@@G@@@G@@@@L(0)      REZ       28                . SPACE FOR A 1 SECTOR READ CU
)@@G@@BUFFER@D@@@@SECTOR    EQUF      L(0)              . SECTOR BUFFER @B@@@@CV
)@@G@@DAS       EQUF      SECTOR            .   @B@@@@L(0)      REZ       1   CW
)@@G@@              .   @E@@@@UTABSZ    EQUF      L(0),,H1          . SIZE OF CX
)@@G@@UNIT TABLE  @H@@@@CURGRP    EQUF      L(0),,S4          . CURRENT FIRST CY
)@@G@@4 BITS OF DAS REL ADDR  @H@@@@DASREL    EQUF      L(0),,T3          . CUCZ
)@@G@@RRENT DAS REL ADDRESS FIRST 8 BITS  @B@@@@L(0)      REZ       1         DA
)@@G@@        .   @G@@@@DIRADD    EQUF      L(0)              . CURRENT DIRECTDB
)@@G@@ORY ADDR IN FDNDI @ @@@@          ON        PACKID    @E@@@@S1PACK    REDC
)@@G@@Z       1                 . PACKID FROM SECTOR 1@E@@@@S1LDAT    REZ     DD
)@@G@@  1                 . LDAT FROM SECTOR 1  @ @@@@          OFF       PACKDE
)@@G@@ID    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.         DEFINITIONS OF FIELDS IN UDF
)@@G@@NIT TABLE   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.         THERE ARE MAXTRK/256 ONE WORD ENDG
)@@G@@TRIES PER UNIT    @G@@@@.         THESE MAKE UP A UNIT ENTRY, AND THERE DH
)@@G@@IS ONE UNIT ENTRY PER   @E@@@@.         UNIT IN THE CONFIGURATION AS DESDI
)@@G@@CRIBED BY THE MCT.@[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         EACH ONE WORD ENTRY POINTSDJ
)@@G@@ TO A SET OF DIRECTORY TRACK ENTRIES@G@@@@.         THE FIRST 4 BITS OF DK
)@@G@@THE DAS RELATIVE ADDRESS IS CONTAINED     @F@@@@.         IN THE ONE WORDL
)@@G@@D UNIT TABLE ENTRY.  THE OTHER EIGHT BITS @C@@@@.         ARE IN THE DIRDM
)@@G@@ECTORY TRACK ENTRY.     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.         A LOOK-UP OF A PARTIDN
)@@G@@CULAR ADDRESS CONSISTS OF     @F@@@@.         INDEXING INTO THE TABLE BADO
)@@G@@SED ON THE LDAT INDEX TIMES   @E@@@@.         THE NUMBER OF ENTRIES PER DP
)@@G@@UNIT (MAXTRK/256).  THIS@F@@@@.         GIVES THE BASE ADDRESS OF THE TADQ
)@@G@@BLE AREA FOR THAT UNIT. @F@@@@.         THE FIRST FOUR BITS OF THE DAS RDR
)@@G@@ELATIVE ADDRESS IS ADDED@F@@@@.         TO THAT TO GIVE THE ADDRESS OF TDS
)@@G@@HE ONE WORD ENTRY OF    @G@@@@.         INTEREST.  THE SET OF DIRECTORY DT
)@@G@@TRACK ENTRIES POINTED TO BY   @F@@@@.         THAT UNIT ENTRY IS THEN SEDU
)@@G@@ARCHED FOR THE MATCHING LOWER @D@@@@.         EIGHT BITS OF THE DAS RELADV
)@@G@@TIVE ADDRESS.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@UNITENT   EQUF      0   DW
)@@G@@              . THE WHOLE ENTRY     @E@@@@LDAT      EQUF      0,0,T1    DX
)@@G@@        . FOR CHECKING ONLY   @G@@@@UNTGRP    EQUF      0,0,S3          DY
)@@G@@  . FIRST FOUR BITS OF DAS REL ADDR @F@@@@UNTDT     EQUF      0,0,H2    DZ
)@@G@@        . POINTS TO DT ENTRY SET    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         THE FOLLEA
)@@G@@OWING ARE DEFINITIONS OF CELLS IN THE LEVEL 33 MCT    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@EB
)@@G@@MCTSIX    EQUF      0,0,T3            . INDEX TO SS STATUS ENTRY  @G@@@@EC
)@@G@@MCTPIX    EQUF      0,0,T2            . INDEX TO SS PATH DESCRIPTORS    ED
)@@G@@@E@@@@TY        EQUF      1,0,S6            . TYPE OF CU FOR SS   @G@@@@EE
)@@G@@MCTEQP    EQUF      0,0,S1            . EQUIP TYPE INDEEX FOR THIS SS   EF
)@@G@@@F@@@@MCTNUM    EQUF      0,0,S2            . NUMBER OF UNITS IN THIS SSEG
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         DIRECTORY TRACK TABLE ENTRIES   @[@@@@.     EH
)@@G@@@H@@@@DASBITS   EQUF      0                 . DAS BITS AND 8 BITS OF DASEI
)@@G@@REL ADDR    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC                EJ
)@@G@@        .   @F@@@@IOW$$*    NAME                        . ER IOW$ AND CHEK
)@@G@@ECK STATUS  @B@@@@          ER        IOW$              .   @B@@@@      EL
)@@G@@    TZ,S1     3,A0              .   @B@@@@          J         P(1,1)    EM
)@@G@@        .   @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC    EN
)@@G@@                    .   @H@@@@STAT*     NAME                        . PREO
)@@G@@OC TO DEFINE STATUS RETURN LOCATIONS@B@@@@STATUS*(P(1,1)) L,U A0,P(1,1) EP
)@@G@@        .   @F@@@@          L         A5,PCW(P(1,1))    . GET PRINT CONTEQ
)@@G@@ROL WORD    @B@@@@          J         0,X11             .   @[@@@@.     ER
)@@G@@@B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@/.    ES
)@@G@@@B@@@@$(1)      LIT                         .   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     ET
)@@G@@@B@@@@FDINTL*                               . $H@F@@@@          LMJ     EU
)@@G@@  A2,READ4          . READ FIRST 4 WRDS OF DIR  @F@@@@          TNZ     EV
)@@G@@  CHECK             . IS THIS A DIRECTORY ?     @F@@@@          TNZ     EW
)@@G@@  LUTLEN            . AND FETCHED BY DGET$ ?    @D@@@@          J       EX
)@@G@@  STATUS(14)        . NO TO EITHER  @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         GET MCT EY
)@@G@@IF NECESSARY@[@@@@.     @G@@@@          L         A0,MCTADD         . $PEZ
)@@G@@ GET ADDRESS OF MCT BUFFER    @F@@@@          LA,U      A1,'MCT'        FA
)@@G@@  . H2 WILL HAVE SYSTEM LEVEL @E@@@@          TNE,H1    A1,0,A0         FB
)@@G@@  . IS THIS A GOOD MCT ?@E@@@@          J         GOTMCT            . YEFC
)@@G@@S, NO NEED GET ONE@E@@@@          LXI,U     A0,3              . MCT$ SUBFD
)@@G@@FUNCTION    @]@@@@DOMCT     . @I@@@@          LA        A1,(3584,0)     FE
)@@G@@  . LENGTH AND OFFSET (INCASE LEVEL 35 EXEC)    @H@@@@          DS      FF
)@@G@@  A0,SECTOR         . BUILD MCT PACKET IN SECTOR BUFFER     @F@@@@      FG
)@@G@@    L,U       A0,SECTOR         . GET ADDRESS OF MCT PACKET @D@@@@      FH
)@@G@@    ER        MCT$              . $P GET MCT    @F@@@@          LA,S1   FI
)@@G@@  A2,0,A0           . GET THE STATUS OF MCT$    @E@@@@          JZ      FJ
)@@G@@  A2,GOTMCT         . EVERYTHING IS OK    @F@@@@          TE,U      A2,4FK
)@@G@@              . IS IT JUST AN OVERRUN     @E@@@@          J         STATFL
)@@G@@US(5)         . NOPE IT'S BAD NEWS  @B@@@@GOTMCT                        FM
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.         COUNT THE NUMBER OF UNITS IN THIFN
)@@G@@S CONFIGURATION   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@          LA        A0,MCTADD       FO
)@@G@@  . RESTORE THIS FOR LATER    @H@@@@          LA,H1     A5,7,A0         FP
)@@G@@  . MASS STORE ID TABLE LEN=UNIT CNT+1    @F@@@@                        FQ
)@@G@@              . +1 BECAUSE NO LDAT IS ZERO@D@@@@          SA        A5,UFR
)@@G@@NITS          . SAVE THE COUNT@F@@@@          MSI,U     A5,MAXTRK/256   FS

)@@G@@  . SAVE ONE FOR FAKE ENTRY AT END  @F@@@@          SA        A5,UTABSZ FU
)@@G@@        . SAVE THE UNIT TABLE SIZE  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.         CALCULATFV
)@@G@@E SIZE OF DIRECTORY TRACK ITEM BUFFER     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@          LAFW
)@@G@@        A4,DLSIZE         . TRACK COUNT FOR DIRECTORY FILE  @G@@@@      FX
)@@G@@    ANA       A4,DT1            . SUBTRACT ADDR OF FIRST TRACK    @G@@@@FY
)@@G@@          AA,U      A4,5              . THROW IN SOME FOR GOOD MEASURE  FZ
)@@G@@@H@@@@          MSI       A4,ENTSIZ         . COMPUTE TOTAL SPACE FOR DAGA
)@@G@@S ENTRIES   @F@@@@          AA        A4,A5             . ADD IN THE UNIGB
)@@G@@T TABLE SIZE@E@@@@          SA        A4,DTISIZ         . SAVE THE TOTALGC
)@@G@@ SIZE @E@@@@          J         STATUS(0)         . $PE SET STATUS TO 0 GD
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@FDRDAS*                       GE
)@@G@@        . $H@F@@@@          L,U       A0,DLPKT          . GET ADDRESS OFGF
)@@G@@ I/O PACKET @H@@@@          SZ        DLTRKS            . $P SET NUMBER GG
)@@G@@OF DT'S PROCESSED TO 0  @F@@@@          L,U       A1,DAS            . $PGH
)@@G@@ SET ACCESS WORD FOR DAS@B@@@@          LXI,U     A1,28             .   GI

)@@G@@ORE   @G@@@@          S         A5,DT1ADD         . $P SAVE ADDRESS OF FGN

)@@G@@    LR        R1,UNITS          . GET THE UNIT COUNT  @D@@@@          LAGP

)@@G@@,U      R2,MAXTRK/256-1   . NUMBER OF ENTRIES-1 PER UNIT    @E@@@@NXTGRPGU

)@@G@@  A1,ENTSIZ         . SET THE INCREMENT FOR DT TABLE  @]@@@@NEWUNT    . HD
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LR,U      R1,1              . TO SET NEW UNIT FLAG@F@@@@HE
)@@G@@          SR        R1,STUNIT         . WE ARE STARTING A UNIT    @ @@@@HF

)@@G@@          S         A5,IODADD @ @@@@          IOW$$     STATUS(3) @F@@@@HI

)@@G@@          DL        A4,DAS+4          . SAVE PACK ID AND    @E@@@@      HK
)@@G@@    DS        A4,S1PACK         . LDAT FROM SECTOR 1  @ @@@@          OFHL
)@@G@@F       PACKID    @D@@@@READAS                                . $P READ HM
)@@G@@A DAS @B@@@@          IOW$$     STATUS(3)         .   @G@@@@          TNHN
)@@G@@Z       STUNIT            . $T IS THIS FIRST DAS ON UNIT?   @E@@@@      HO
)@@G@@    J         NOTDT1            . $A YES NO,NOTDT1    @F@@@@          SZHP
)@@G@@        STUNIT            . THIS IS NO LONGER NEW     @ @@@@          ONHQ
)@@G@@        PACKID    @E@@@@          L,H1      A4,DAS            . LDAT OF HR
)@@G@@THIS UNIT   @E@@@@          L         A2,MCTADD         . MCT BUFFER ADDHS
)@@G@@RESS  @B@@@@          TG,U      A4,1              .   @E@@@@          TGHT
)@@G@@,H1     A4,7,A2           . CHECK LDAT IN RANGE @H@@@@          J       HU
)@@G@@  NOFPAX            . NOT IN RANGE, LEAVE FIXPAX TBL ALONE  @F@[@@      HV
)@@G@@    TE,H1     A4,S1LDT          . SAME LDAT IN SECTOR 1?    @F@@@[      HW
)@@G@@    TE,H1     A4,S1LDAT         . SAME LDAT IN SECTOR 1?    @E@@@@      HX
)@@G@@    J         NOFPAX            . NO, MAYBE NOT DISK  @G@@@@          A,HY
)@@G@@H2      A2,7,A2           . POINT TO FIXPAX TABLE IN MCT    @G@@@@      HZ
)@@G@@    A         A2,A4             . POINT TO ENTRY FOR THIS UNIT    @F@@@@IA
)@@G@@          L         A4,S1PACK         . GET PACKID FROM SECTOR 1  @G@@@@IB
)@@G@@          TNZ       0,A2              . AND IF NOTHING IS THERE YET     IC
)@@G@@@F@@@@          S         A4,0,A2           . THEN PUT IT INTO TABLE    ID
)@@G@@@]@@@@NOFPAX    . @ @@@@          OFF       PACKID    @G[@@@          LXIE
)@@G@@,H1     A2,DAS            . GET LDAT INDEX OF THIS UNIT     @F@@@@      IF
)@@G@@    TG        A2,UNITS          . IS THIS A VALID LDAT INDEX@E@@@@      IG
)@@G@@    J         STATUS(14)        . NO, SOME ONE BLEW IT@G@@@@          SZIH

)@@G@@@[@@@@/.    @G@@@@.         SUBROUTINE TO READ THE FIRST THREE WORDS OF SW

)@@G@@@B@@@^.         CALL SOPEN ( KEYS, SLEN, SAREA )@[@@@^.     @E@@@^.     YB

)@@G@@@[@@@^.     @D@@@^.                   MITEM: MAIN ITEM TO BE SORTED     YI

)@@G@@    AXR$,1    .   @F@@@^MISIZE    EQU       37                . LENGTH OYL
)@@G@@F RECORD TO SORT  @B@@@^SOPEN*    S         X11,SX11          .   @B@@@^YM
)@@G@@          SZ        A3                .   @F@@@^          L         A1,*YN
)@@G@@0,X11         . $P INITIALIZE SORT KEYS   @B@@@^          L,U       A0,BYO
)@@G@@YQF           .   @B@@@^          TNE,U     A1,1              .   @B@@@^YP
)@@G@@          L,U       A0,BYACCT         .   @B@@@^          TNE,U     A1,2YQ
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@^          L,U       A0,BYREEL         .   @B@@@^YR
)@@G@@          S,H2      A0,SRTPKT+4       .   @F@@@^          L         A0,*YS

)@@G@@OCATION OF SORT AREA    @B@@@^          S,H2      A0,SRTPKT+2       .   YV
)@@G@@@E@@@^          L,U       A0,ASG            . $P ASSIGN SORT FILE @B@@@^YW
)@@G@@          ER        CSF$              .   @B@@@^          JP        A0,OYX
)@@G@@PEN           .   @B@@@^          ER        ERR$              .   @D@@@^YY

)@@G@@U       A0,1              . $P SET FLAG TO 1    @B@@@^          S       ZA

)@@G@@,U      A0,1              . $T IS FLAG SET TO 1?@E@@@^          J       ZN

)@@G@@              . $P PERFORM SORT     @B@@@^SRTRET                        ZP
)@@G@@        .   @E@@@^          L,U       A0,2              . $P SET FLAG TOZQ

)@@G@@        ERR$              .   @F@@@^          R$RET     DONE            ZT
)@@G@@  . $P GET RECORD FROM SORT   @F@@@^                                    ZU
)@@G@@  . $T WAS A RECORD RETURNED? @D@@@^                                    ZV
)@@G@@  . $A YES NO,DONE@B@@@^          L         X11,SX11          .   @G@@@^ZW
)@@G@@          A,U       A0,1              . $P CALCULATE INDEX OF RECORD    ZX
)@@G@@@B@@@^          AN,H2     A0,SRTPKT+2       .   @B@@@^          S       ZY
)@@G@@  A0,*0,X11         .   @B@@@^          J         3,X11             . $EZZ
)@@G@@@B@@@^DONE      L         X11,SX11          .   @E@@@^          SZ      AA
)@@G@@  FLAG              . $P SET FLAG TO 0    @B@@@^          J         1,X1AB
)@@G@@1             . $E@B@@@^$(0)                                  .   @B@@@^AC
)@@G@@SX11      +         0                 .   @B@@@^FLAG      +         0   AD
)@@G@@              .   @C@@@^ASG       '@ASG,T MY-SORT-FILE,F/1//5000 . '    AE
)@@G@@@B@@@^SRTPKT    R$FILE                      ;   @B@@@^          'CORE',1AF
)@@G@@                    ;   @B@@@^          'RSZW',MISIZE               ;   AG
)@@G@@@B@@@^          'COPY',BYACCT               ;   @B@@@^          'FILES',AH

)@@G@@@B@A@^          'LPOC',SRTRET               .   @B@@@A          'LPOC',SAJ
)@@G@@RTRET               ;   @G@B@A          'NODISK' 'NOTAPE' 'DELCON' 'DELLAK
)@@G@@OG . TURN OFF UNNEEDED STUFF  @G@C@B          'NODISK' 'NOTAPE' 'DELCON'AL
)@@G@@ 'DELLOG' . TURN OFF UNNEEDED STUFF @F@@@C          'NODISK' 'NOTAPE' 'DAM

)@@G@@        ; SORT BY ACCOUNT NUMBER    @G@@@^          'KEYW',8,35,72,'A','AO
)@@G@@A'      ; TWELVE CHARACTERS OF ACCOUNT    @B@@@^          'COPY',BYQF   AP
)@@G@@              .   @E@@@^BYREEL    R$FILE                      ; SORT BY AQ
)@@G@@BACK-UP REEL@D@@@^          'KEYW',33,35,36,'A','A'     ; BACK-UP REEL  AR
)@@G@@@F@@@^          'KEYW',32,23,12,'U','A'     . FILE POSITION ON REEL     AS
)@@G@@@G@@@^BYQF      R$FILE                      ; SORT BY QUALIFIER, NAME, CAT
)@@G@@YCLE  @D@@@^          'KEYW',2,35,72,'A','A'      ; QUALIFIER     @D@@@^AU
)@@G@@          'KEYW',4,35,72,'A','A'      ; FILE NAME     @C@@@^          'KAV
)@@G@@EYW',18,11,12,'U','A'     . F-CYCLE @#@@@^          END     _@@@@@@@@@@@AW
)@@G@@      IF(STATUS.LT.0) GO*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@.     @D@@@@.         CALL DGEAX
)@@G@@T(FILENAME,BUFFERS,ASTAT,MSTAT)     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         THIS SUBAY
)@@G@@ROUTINE DETERMINES THE INITIAL RESERVE REQUIRED TO    @F@@@@.         DOAZ
)@@G@@ A DGET$ FUNCTION OF THE ER MSCON$.  THEN A TEMPORARY @G@@@@.         FIBA
)@@G@@LE IS ASSIGNED WITH THAT INITIAL RESERVE.  IF THE ASSIGN    @F@@@@.     BB
)@@G@@    STATUS IS POSITIVE AND IF THE ASSIGN STATUS BITS ARE    @F@@@@.     BC
)@@G@@    ACCEPTABLE TO THE CALLER, A DGET$ FUNCTION IS PERFORMED.@[@@@@.     BD
)@@G@@@F@@@@.         FILENAME IS AN ARRAY DIMENSIONED AT 2 WHICH CONTAINS THEBE
)@@G@@@E@@@@.         NAME OF THE FILE TO ASSIGN AND USE FOR THE DGET$. @[@@@@BF
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@.         BUFFERS IS AN ARRAY DIMENSIONED AT 3590 WHICH WILLBG
)@@G@@ BE USED    @ @@@@.         BY THIS SUBROUTINE. @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     BH
)@@G@@    ASTAT IS A VARIABLE SET BY THE CALLER TO INDICATE WHICH @F@@@@.     BI
)@@G@@    ASSIGN STATUS BITS WILL CAUSE THE DGET$ TO BE OMITTED.  @G@@@@.     BJ
)@@G@@    IF ASTAT IS SET TO 0, THE DGET$ WILL BE DONE IF THE ASSIGN    @G@@@@BK
)@@G@@.         STATUS IS POSITIVE.  IF ASTAT IS SET TO 100000000000 (OCTAL), BL
)@@G@@@G@@@@.         THE DGET$ WILL NOT BE DONE IF THE FILE WAS ALREADY ASSIGBM
)@@G@@NED.  @E@@@@.         ON EXIT, ASTAT WILL BE SET TO THE ASSIGN STATUS.  BN
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         MSTAT IS A VARIABLE WHICH IS SET TO 0 IF THEBO
)@@G@@ DGET$ IS NOT     @G@@@@.         DONE OR TO THE STATUS (A0) RETURNED FRBP
)@@G@@OM MSCON$ IF THE DGET$  @^@@@@.         WAS DONE.     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@BQ
)@@G@@.         CALL SDGET(FILENAME,BUFFERS,ASTAT,MSTAT)    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@BR
)@@G@@.         THIS SUBROUTINE PERFORMS EXACTLY AS DGET DOES, EXCEPT THAT    BS
)@@G@@@G@@@@.         THE RESULTING FILE IS CREATED BY THE UOM FUNCTION OF MSCBT
)@@G@@ON$,  @ @@@@.         SDGET$ (CODE 7).    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.         CABU
)@@G@@LL DGETP(PACKID,EQUIP,FILENAME,ASTAT,MSTAT)     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.     BV
)@@G@@    THE SUBROUTINE PERFORMS A DGETP$ REQUEST ON THE PACKID NAMED  @G@@@@BW
)@@G@@.         MOUNTING THAT PACK ON THE EQUIPMENT TYPE PROVIDED.  THE FILE  BX
)@@G@@@B@@@@.         IS ASIGNED ON THE PACK AS WELL. @H@@@@.         IN ALL OBY
)@@G@@THER RESPECTS, THE SUBROUTINE PERFORMS EXACTLY AS DGET DOES.@[@@@@.     BZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@          AXR$,1                      .   @#@@@@      CA
)@@G@@    IOPROC  @G@#@@DGET$S    EQU       010               . OLD SINGLE BUFCB
)@@G@@FERED VERSION     @E@@@@SDGET$    EQU       007               . BET MAINCC
)@@G@@ ITEMS ONLY @[@@@@.     @B@@@@$(1)                                  .   CD
)@@G@@@E@@@@DGETP*                                . ENTRY TO DO A DGETP$@G@@@@CE
)@@G@@          SZ        A3                . CLEAR FOR FORTRAN COMPATABILITY CF
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LA        A4,*1,X11         . GET EQUIP TYPE LJSF @G@@@@CG
)@@G@@          LA        A1,*0,X11         . GET PACKID FOR FILE AND DGETP$  CH
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA,U      A0,DGETP$         . FUNCTION FOR REM PACK GET CI
)@@G@@@H@@@@          AX,U      X11,2             . BUMP X11 TO LOOK LIKE NORMCJ
)@@G@@AL DGET     @^@@@@          LR,U      R1,5@D@@@@EQUIPL    AND,U     A4,0CK
)@@G@@77            . ISOLATE A CHAR@F@@@@          TE,U      A5,' '          CL
)@@G@@  . DONE IF ITS NOT BLANK     @F@@@@          J         GETD1           CM
)@@G@@  . START REGULAR PROCESSING  @D@@@@          SSC       A4,6            CN
)@@G@@  . GET A NEW CHAR@G@@@@          JGD       R1,EQUIPL         . LOOP BACCO
)@@G@@K IF WE HAVE ANY LEFT   @G@@@@          J         GETD1             . ELCP
)@@G@@SE CONTINUE WITH BLANK EQUIP  @E@@@@SDGET*    LA,U      A0,SDGET$       CQ
)@@G@@  . SHORT DGET FUNCTION @C@@@@          J         GETD              . COCR
)@@G@@NTINUE@E@@@@DGET*     LA,U      A0,DGET$          . STOCK DGET FUNCTION CS
)@@G@@@E@@@@GETD      LA        A1,('  .   ')     . TO TERM @ASG IMAGE  @F@@@@CT
)@@G@@          LA        A4,('     F')     . EQUIP TYPE TO @ASG ON     @F@@@@CU
)@@G@@          SZ        A3                . FOR FORTRAN COMPATABILITY @G@@@@CV
)@@G@@GETD1     SA        A1,PACKID         . SET A PACKID OR TERM @ASG IMAGE CW
)@@G@@@G@@@@          SA        A4,EQUIP          . SET THE SCRATCH FILE EQUIPCX
)@@G@@ TYPE @E@@@@          DL        A4,*0,X11         . $P GET FILE NAME    CY
)@@G@@@G@@@@          L         R1,*2,X11         . $P GET UNACCEPTABLE ASG BICZ
)@@G@@TS    @F@@@@          L,U       A3,*1,X11         . $P GET ADDRESS OF BUDA
)@@G@@FFER  @F@@@@          SZ        R3                . $P INDICATE DGET$ NODB
)@@G@@T DONE@F@@@@          DS        A4,1,A3           . SET FILE NAME IN PACDC
)@@G@@KET   @E@@@@          S         A0,0,A3           . $P PUT IT IN PACKET DD
)@@G@@@F@@@@          L,U       A2,5,A3           . $P GET BUFFER ADDRESSES   DE
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA        A4,PACKID         . GET THE REM DISK PACKID   DF
)@@G@@@B@@@@          LXI,U     A2,1792,A2        .   @F@@@@          SA      DG
)@@G@@  A4,5,A3           . STORE IT IN THE PACKET    @F@@@@          S       DH
)@@G@@  A2,4,A3           . $P PUT THEM IN PACKET     @H@@@@          SX      DI
)@@G@@  A2,3,A3           . FOR SDGET$, THEY GO IN ANOTHER PLACE  @G@@@@      DJ
)@@G@@    TNE,U     A0,SDGET$         . ARE WE DOING A SHORT DGET ?     @I@@@@DK
)@@G@@          J         DOASG             . YES, WE DON'T NEED TO GET DIRECTDL
)@@G@@ORY SIZE    @G@@@@          SZ        3,A3              . MAKE SURE TRACDM
)@@G@@K REQUIRED CLEAR  @B@@@@GETDSZ    L,U       A0,0,A3           .   @E@@@@DN
)@@G@@          DL        A4,1,A3           . SAVE THE FILE NAME  @F@@@@      DO
)@@G@@    SZ        1,A3              . CLEAR FILE NAME IN PACKET @F@@@@      DP
)@@G@@    SZ        2,A3              . SO WE DON'T DO DGET NOW   @D@@@@      DQ
)@@G@@    ER        MSCON$            . $P ER MSCON$  @E@@@@          DS      DR
)@@G@@  A4,1,A3           . RESTORE FILE NAME   @F@@@@                        DS
)@@G@@              . GET INITIAL RESERVE NEEDED@F@#@@          SSL       A0,3DT
)@@G@@0             . $P GET EXEC INDICATOR     @G@#@@          TNE,U     A0,0DU
)@@G@@40            . IS THIS LEVEL 33 OR HIGHER ?    @F@#@@          J       DV
)@@G@@  $+3               . YES, FORGET OTHER TEST    @G@#@@          TLE,U   DW
)@@G@@  A0,043            . $T EXEC ALLOW DOUBLE BUFFERS?   @E@#@@          J DX
)@@G@@        SINGLE            . $A YES NO,SINGLE    @F@@@@          L       DY
)@@G@@  A0,3,A3           . $P GET INITIAL RESERVE    @B@@@@          L       DZ
)@@G@@  A1,A0             .   @B@@@@          SSL       A1,5              .   EA
)@@G@@@B@@@@          TLE,U     A1,6              .   @B@@@@          L,U     EB
)@@G@@  A1,6              .   @F@@@@          A         A0,A1             . $PEC
)@@G@@ ADD SOME EXTRA TRACKS  @E@@@@          L,U       A2,5              . $PED
)@@G@@ CONVERT TO OCTAL @B@@@@LOOP      DSL       A0,3              .   @B@@@@EE
)@@G@@          SSL       A1,3              .   @B@@@@          JGD       A2,LEF
)@@G@@OOP           .   @B@@@@          A         A1,('000000')     .   @E@@@@EG
)@@G@@          S         A1,INRES          . $P PUT IN ASG IMAGE @F@@@@DOASG EH
)@@G@@    DL        A0,1,A3           . $P RIGHT ADJUST FILE NAME @B@@@@      EI
)@@G@@    L,U       A4,11             .   @[@@@@NOP   @B@@@@NEXTCH    AND,U   EJ
)@@G@@  A1,077            .   @B@@@@          TE,U      A2,' '            .   EK
)@@G@@@B@@@@          J         RIGHT             .   @B@@@@          DSC     EL
)@@G@@  A0,6              .   @B@@@@          JGD       A4,NEXTCH         .   EM
)@@G@@@G@@@@RIGHT     DS        A0,FNAME          . $P PUT FILE NAME IN ASG IMEN
)@@G@@AGE   @B@@@@ASGIT     L,U       A0,ASG            .   @B@@@@          EREO
)@@G@@        CSF$              .   @F@@@@          L         R2,A0           EP
)@@G@@  . $P SAVE ASSIGN STATUS     @F@@@@          JN        A0,EXIT         EQ
)@@G@@  . $T ASSIGN SUCCESSFUL?     @D@@@@                                    ER
)@@G@@  . $A YES NO,EXIT@G@@@@          AND       A0,R1             . $P GET UES
)@@G@@NACCEPTABLE ASG BITS    @G@@@@          JZ        A1,GETDIR         . IFET
)@@G@@ @ASG STAT NOT OK, GET DIR    @E@@@@          DL        A1,1,A3         EU
)@@G@@  . GET THE FILE NAME   @G@@@@          LA        A0,4,A3           . BUEV
)@@G@@ILD PACKET WHERE MSCON BUF IS @F@@@@          DS        A1,IONAME       EW
)@@G@@  . SET FILE NAME IN PACKET   @D@@@@          LA,U      A1,IODADD+1     EX
)@@G@@  . ADDR OF BUFFER@E@@@@          LA,U      A2,R$             . WE WILL EY
)@@G@@DO A READ   @D@@@@          LXI,U     A1,3              . READ 3 WORDS  EZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@          SZ        IODADD            . STARTING AT SECTOR ZERO   FA
)@@G@@@F@@@@          SA        A2,IOFUNC         . SET THE READ FUNCTION     FB
)@@G@@@E@@@@          SA        A1,IOACW          . AND THE ACCESS WORD @E@@@@FC
)@@G@@          ER        IOW$              . WAIT FOR THE I/O    @D@@@@      FD
)@@G@@    TZ        IOSTAT            . READ GO OK ?  @F@@@@          J       FE
)@@G@@  GETDIR            . HE GETS WHAT HE ASKED FOR @C@@@@          LA,U    FF
)@@G@@  A2,1              . A FLAG  @F@@@@          TZ        1,A1            FG
)@@G@@  . IS THIS AN SDGET$ FILE ?  @H@@@@          LA,U      A2,0            FH
)@@G@@  . NO, IT HAS NON ZERO LOOK UP TAB LEN   @D@@@@          LA,U      A0,SFI
)@@G@@DGET$         . FOR TESTING   @D@@@@          LA,U      A1,1            FJ
)@@G@@  . ANOTHER FLAG  @G@@@@          TE        A0,0,A3           . DO WE WAFK
)@@G@@NT TO DO AN SDGET$ ?    @E@@@@          LA,U      A1,0              . NOFL
)@@G@@, CLEAR THE FLAG  @G@@@@          TNE,U     A1,0,A2           . ARE BOTHFM
)@@G@@ DGET$ OR BOTH SDGET$ ? @F@@@@          J         EXIT              . YEFN
)@@G@@S, WE GOT WHAT WE WANT  @G@@@@          LA        A4,('@FREE ')     . WEFO
)@@G@@ WILL CHANGE @ASG,T TO @FREE  @D@@@@          LA        A5,ASG          FP
)@@G@@  . SAVE @ASG,T   @F@@@@          LA,U      A2,' . '          . TO STOP FQ
)@@G@@CSI1 ON @FREE     @F@@@@          SA        A4,ASG            . SET TO GFR
)@@G@@ET RID OF FILE    @D@@@@          LA        A4,FNAME+2        . SAVE ',FFS
)@@G@@/   ' @F@@@@          LA,U      A0,ASG            . POINT AT THE CSF IMAFT
)@@G@@GE    @F@@@@          SA,H1     A2,FNAME+2        . PUT BLANK PERIOD BLAFU
)@@G@@NK IN @F@@@@          ER        CSF$              . START WITH A NEW FILFV
)@@G@@E     @E@@@@          SA        A4,FNAME+2        . RESTORE ',F/   '    FW
)@@G@@@D@@@@          SA        A5,ASG            . RESTORE @ASG,T@H@@@@      FX
)@@G@@    JNZ       A1,ASGIT          . IF SDGET$ WANTED, NO SIZE COMPUTATION FY
)@@G@@@F@@@@          J         GETDSZ            . NEED INITIAL RES FOR DGET$FZ
)@@G@@@B@@@@GETDIR    L,U       A0,0,A3           .   @D@@@@          ER      GA
)@@G@@  MSCON$            . $P ER MSCON$ .@E@@@@          L         R3,A0     GB
)@@G@@        . $P SAVE DGET$ STATUS@B@@@@EXIT                                GC
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          SZ        A3                .   @F@@@@          S GD
)@@G@@        R2,*2,X11         . $P RETURN ASSIGN STATUS   @F@@@@          S GE
)@@G@@        R3,*3,X11         . $P RETURN DGET STATUS     @B@@@@          J GF
)@@G@@        5,X11             . $E@F@#@@SINGLE    L,U       A0,DGET$S       GG
)@@G@@  . $P GET SINGLE DGET$ CODE  @E@#@@          S         A0,0,A3         GH
)@@G@@  . $P PUT IN PACKET    @B@#@@          J         DOASG             .   GI
)@@G@@@B@@@@$(0)                                  .   @^@@@@ASG       '@ASG,T GJ
)@@G@@'     @^@@@@FNAME     +0D       .   @^@@@@          ',      '     @E@@@@GK
)@@G@@EQUIP     +         0                 . FILL IN AT RUN TIME @#@@@@      GL
)@@G@@    '/     '@#@]@@INRES     '     1'@#@@@]INRES     '    20'@^@[@@      GM
)@@G@@    '//1000,'     @^@^@[          '//4000,'     @^@@@^          '//8000,GN
)@@G@@'     @^@@@@PACKID    '       . '   @#@@@@          END     _@@@@@IF (APGO
)@@G@@STAT(MITEM).EQ.0) GO TO 520   >@@@@C@A@@@1@@@@@@      CALL ECHAR(EDPKT,'GP
)@@G@@/')   >@@@@A@B@@@1@@@@@@      CALL EFD1(EDPKT,AC)@@[U@@@@@@@            GQ

)@@G@@@@^@@]@@A@@]@@E@@\@#A@@[@@E@@@@@@@C.IOW$        TDATE$      APTIA       JE
)@@G@@@@[@@@@@@@^/APTID       @@[@@@@@@@BAAPTIS       @@[@@@@@@@#<APTNL       JF

)@@G@@. THE FOLLOWING SET OF ROUTINES INITIALIZES (FORK), DISPACTCHES (STACT) IL
)@@G@@@G@@@R. AND HANDLES THE CONTINGENCIES (PROCON) FOR THE ACTIVITIES WHICH IM
)@@G@@@ASG, @C@@@R. EXAMINE, AND MAKE CALLS TO PACK$ AND PREP$.   @[@@@R.     IN
)@@G@@@F@@@R. ACTIVITIES ARE QUEUED AT THE LABEL STACT BY THE CELL QACT.  WHENIO
)@@G@@@F@@@R. THE MAIN ACTIVITY ENTERS THE FORTRAN CALLABLE ROUTINE ASGPCK, ITIP
)@@G@@@E@@@R. ACTIVITATES AN ACTIVITY QUEUED ON THAT CELL.  THIS ROUTINE@G@@@RIQ
)@@G@@. TRADES MAIN ITEM ENTRIES (WITH A FEW MORE WORDS ADDED FOR FLAGS) WITH IR
)@@G@@@G@@@R. THE MAIN ACTIVITY AND THEN ALLOWS THE MAIN ACTIVITY TO RETURN TOIS
)@@G@@ THE  @F@@@R. CALLER BY ACTIVATING THE ACTIVITY QUEUED ON THE CELL QMAINIT
)@@G@@.     @D@@@R. BOTH QUEUES ARE FLAGGED AS IN USE DURING ROUTINE    @F@@@RIU
)@@G@@. INITIATION IN ORDER TO INSURE THAT THE FIRST ACTIVITY IS QUEUED @F@@@RIV
)@@G@@. PROPERLY.  IF WORD ONE OF THE MAIN ITEM RECEIVED BY THE NON-MAIN@G@@@RIW
)@@G@@. ACTIVITY IS ZERO, IT IS INTERPRETED AS A FLAG TO HALT AND THE ACTIVITYIX
)@@G@@@F@@@R. DOES AN EXIT$.  THE FIRST N TRANSFERS, WHERE N IS THE NUMBER OF IY
)@@G@@@G@@@R. ACTIVITIES, WILL PASS GARBAGE TO THE MAIN ACTIVITY.  IF THE BUFFIZ

)@@G@@.    BE LOADED    @^@@@R.    BE ON FIXED STORAGE@B@@@R.    BE ON FASTRANSO

)@@G@@    TNZ       ASSIGN            . SHOULD WE @ASG ANY FILES ?@F@@@R      BT
)@@G@@    J         STACT             . NO, GET THE NEXT ITEM     @G@@@R      BU
)@@G@@    J         CHKASG            . YES, SEE IF THIS IS ONE TO @ASG @[@@@RBV
)@@G@@/     @^@@@R. MISCELLANEOUS ROUTINES@[@@@R.     @[@@@R.     @D@@@R. FREEBW
)@@G@@              PERFORMS AN @FREE OF THE FILE     @[@@@R.     @D@@@RFREE  BX
)@@G@@                                . ENTRY POINT   @F@@@R          TP      BY
)@@G@@  FCODE,X10         . SHOULD WE DO ANYTHING ?   @G@@@R          J       BZ
)@@G@@  0,X11             . NO, WE HAD IT OR NEVER GOT IT   @E@@@R          SXCA
)@@G@@        X11,SVX11,X10     . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @E@@@R          LMJ     CB
)@@G@@  X11,SETEPKT       . GET AN EDIT$ PACKET @D@@@R          E$DIT     EPKTCC
)@@G@@,X10          . START EEDITING@E@@@R          E$COPY    5,('@FREE ')    CD
)@@G@@  . START THE IMAGE     @E@@@R          LX        A2,FCODE,X10      . GECE
)@@G@@T THE @FREE CODE  @G@@@R          E$COPY    6,FREEOPT,A2      . MOVE OPTCF
)@@G@@IONS ACCORDING TO A2    @F@@@R          TNZ       FCODE,X10         . DICG
)@@G@@D WE HAVE ANY OPTIONS ? @F@@@R          J         FREE1             . NOCH
)@@G@@, USE THE EXTERNAL NAME @F@@@R          E$FD2     INTFN,X10         . COCI
)@@G@@PY THE INTERNAL NAME    @E@@@R          E$COPY    3,(' .    ')      . TECJ
)@@G@@RMINATE THE IMAGE @E@@@R          J         FREE2             . PERFORM CK
)@@G@@THE @FREE   @G@@@RFREE1     LMJ       X11,FILNAM        . EDIT IN THE CUCL
)@@G@@RRENT FILE NAME   @D@@@RFREE2     LX,H2     A0,EPKT,X10       . IMAGE ADCM
)@@G@@DRESS @D@@@R          LX        X11,SVX11,X10     . RESTORE X11   @D@@@RCN
)@@G@@          ER        CSF$              . DO THE @FREE  @C@@@R          J CO
)@@G@@        0,X11             . RETURN  @[@@@R.     @[@@@R.     @E@@@R. SETECP
)@@G@@PKT           CREATES AN EDIT$ PACKET AT EPKT,X10     @[@@@R.     @E@@@RCQ
)@@G@@SETEPKT   LA,U      A0,EPKT+6,X10     . ADDRESS OF IMAGE    @G@@@R      CR
)@@G@@    LXI,U     A0,'&'*/6+8       . EIGHT WORDS LONG, & FOR MSG     @F@@@RCS
)@@G@@          SZ,H2     EPKT+2,X10        . CLEAR FLAGS IN THE PACKET @D@@@RCT
)@@G@@          SA        A0,EPKT,X10       . SET IN PACKET @C@@@R          J CU
)@@G@@        0,X11             . RETURN  @[@@@R.     @[@@@R.     @D@@@R. ASG CV
)@@G@@              @ASG THE FILE WITH OPTIONS IN A0  @[@@@R.     @[@@@R.     CW
)@@G@@@D@@@RASG       SX        X11,SVX11,X10     . SAVE RETURN   @F@@@R      CX
)@@G@@    LA        A7,A0             . SAVE SPECIFIED OPTIONS    @E@@@R      CY
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,SETEPKT       . GET THE EDIT$ PACKET@D@@@R          E$CZ
)@@G@@DIT     EPKT,X10          . START EDITING @D@@@R          E$COPY    5,('DA
)@@G@@@ASG, ')      . COMMAND FIELD @E@@@R          E$FD1     A7              DB
)@@G@@  . COPY THE OPTIONS    @E@@@R          E$CHAR    ' '               . SPDC
)@@G@@ACE FOR DELIMITER @G@@@R          LMJ       X11,FILNAM        . CURRENT DD
)@@G@@FILE NAME INTO IMAGE    @D@@@R          LX        X11,SVX11,X10     . REDE
)@@G@@STOR RETURN @E@@@R          LA,U      A1,1              . FOR A FLAG LATDF
)@@G@@ER    @E@@@R          LX,H2     A0,EPKT,X10       . ADDRESS OF IMAGE    DG
)@@G@@@C@@@R          ER        CSF$              . @ASG    @G@@@R          SZDH
)@@G@@        FCODE,X10         . SET FREE CODE TO NO OPTIONS     @F@@@R      DI
)@@G@@    JN        A0,$+2            . CHANGE TO NOP IF REJ @ASG @G@@@R      DJ
)@@G@@    TEP       A0,(1*/33)        . WAS THE FILE ALREADY ASSIGNED ? @G@@@RDK
)@@G@@          SNA       A1,FCODE,X10      . YES, CHANGE FREE CODE TO NOP    DL
)@@G@@@D@@@R          SA        A0,ASGBITS,X10    . @ASG STATUS   @D@@@R      DM
)@@G@@    SA        A1,APFLG,X10      . SET @ASG DONE @C@@@R          J       DN
)@@G@@  0,X11             . RETURN  @[@@@R.     @[@@@R.     @F@@@R. ASGOPT    DO
)@@G@@        PLACE PROPER @ASG OPTIONS IN A0 FOR NO PACK   @[@@@R.     @[@@@RDP
)@@G@@.     @F@@@RASGOPT    LA        A1,FLAG3,X10      . GET FILE DESCRIPTOR DQ
)@@G@@FLAGS @G@@@R          LA        A0,('AQZY  ')     . TENTATIVELY GET THE DR
)@@G@@'Y' OPT     @F@@@R          TOP       A1,RLOUT          . IS THE FILE RODS
)@@G@@LLED OUT ?  @D@T@R          TEP,U     A1,010            . OR ON DISK ?  DT
)@@G@@@D@U@T          TEP       A1,REMF           . OR ON DISK ?  @F@@@U      DU
)@@G@@    TEP       A1,REMF           . OR ON REMOVABLE DISK ?    @G@@@R      DV
)@@G@@    J         0,X11             . YES TO EITHER,RETURN AND USE 'Y'@E@T@RDW
)@@G@@          TG,U      A1,040            . IS THIS FILE TAPE ? @E@@@T      DX
)@@G@@    TOP       A1,TAPEF          . IS THIS FILE TAPE ? @E@@@R          LXDY
)@@G@@M,U     A0,'   '          . NO, ERASE 'Y' OPTION@C@@@R          J       DZ
)@@G@@  0,X11             . RETURN  @[@@@R.     @[@@@R.     @F@@@R. FILNAM    EA
)@@G@@        EDIT THE FILE NAME INTO CURRENT EDIT$ IMAGE   @[@@@R.     @[@@@REB
)@@G@@.     @E@@@RFILNAM    SX        X11,FNAMR,X10     . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS EC
)@@G@@@D@@@R          E$FD2     1,X10             . QUALIFIER     @D@@@R      ED
)@@G@@    E$CHAR    '*'               . DELIMETER     @D@@@R          E$FD2   EE
)@@G@@  3,X10             . FILE NAME     @F@@@R          E$CHAR    '('       EF
)@@G@@        . DELIMETER FOR F CYCLE     @E@@@R          E$DECV    17,X10,T3 EG
)@@G@@        . ABSOLUTE F CYCLE    @D@@@R          E$COPY    6,('). .  ')    EH
)@@G@@  . TERMINATORS   @D@@@R          LX        X11,FNAMR,X10     . RETURN AEI
)@@G@@DDRESS@D@@@R          J         0,X11             . JUMP TO IT    @[@@@REJ
)@@G@@.     @[@@@R.     @F@@@R. LOGIT             PERFORM CSF$ TO @LOG CURRENTEK
)@@G@@ MSG, STASH CODES @G@@@R.                   ACTION CODE (IN THIS CASE 'IEL
)@@G@@O' OR 'BP') IS IN A4    @E@@@R.                   AND STATUS (BSP OR I/OEM
)@@G@@) MUST BE IN A5.  @[@@@R.     @[@@@R.     @F@@@RLOGIT     SX        X11,EN

)@@G@@CTSTAT,X10    . SAVE IN THE RETURN PACKET @F@@@R          E$COLN        EQ

)@@G@@SVX11,X10     . RESTORE RETURN@E@@@R          DSA       A0,36           ES

)@@G@@@B@@@R          ON        DEBUG             .   @F@@@R          ER      EX
)@@G@@  PRINT$            . TELL US WHAT WE @LOGGED   @F@@@R          LXI,U   EY

)@@G@@  DEBUG             .   @D@@@R          ER        CSF$              . DOFA

)@@G@@          END     _@@@@@FILE NAME   >@@@@H@F@@@Q@@@@@@          LX,H2   FC
)@@G@@  A0,EPKT,X10       . ADDRES OF IMAGE     >@@@@F@G@@@Q@@@@@@          LAFD
)@@G@@,U      A3,2            *[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@6C     @G@@@6C     THIS PROGRAMFE
)@@G@@ LISTS INFORMATION ABOUT ALL FILES IN AN EXEC-8 FILE  @G@@@6C     DIRECTFF
)@@G@@ORY.  NORMALLY, A COPY OF THE CURRENT DIRECTORY IS OBTAINED @F@@@6C     FG
)@@G@@VIA THE DGET$ FUNCTION OF THE MSCON$ EXECUTIVE REQUEST.     @[@@@6C     FH
)@@G@@@F@@@6C     NORMALLY FILES ARE SORTED BY QUALIFIER, NAME, AND F-CYCLE.  FI
)@@G@@@[@@@6C     @G@@@6C     THE EXECUTION OF THE PROGRAM IS CONTROLLED BY SEFJ
)@@G@@TTING THE MIDDLE  @G@@@6C     THIRD OF THE RUN'S CONDITION WORD.  THIS IFK
)@@G@@S DONE WITH THE COMMAND @E@@@6C     '@SETC XXX ' WHERE XXX MAY HAVE THE FL
)@@G@@FOLLOWING VALUES: @[@@@6C     @F@@@6C     0001  SORT FILES BY ACCOUNT NUFM
)@@G@@MBER, QUALIFIER, NAME, F-CYCLE@G@@@6C     0002  READ A FILE DIRECTORY FRFN
)@@G@@OM A SECURE DIRECTORY TAPE THAT     @E@@@6C           IS ASSIGNED TO THEFO
)@@G@@ RUN WITH THE NAME 'DTAPE'.   @E@@@6C     0004  LIST ONLY FILES WHICH ARFP
)@@G@@E MARKED AS DISABLED    @G@@@6C     0010  ASSIGN AND FREE CERTAIN FILES FQ
)@@G@@AS DETERMINED BY THE ROUTINE  @F@@@6C           ASGPCK.  AS OF THIS WRITFR
)@@G@@ING, FILES WHICH HAVEN'T BEEN @F@@@6C           BACKED-UP OR USER ASSIGNFS
)@@G@@ED IN 24 HRS WILL BE ASSIGNED,@G@@@6C           BUT WITHOUT UPDATING THEFT
)@@G@@ TLR STAMP.  THIS IS DONE AT UOM    @D@@@6C           FOR PURPOSES OF MAFU
)@@G@@SS STORAGE BILLING.     @D@@@6C     0020  SORT BY BACKUP REEL, POSITION FV
)@@G@@ON REEL     @D@@@6C     0040  PRINT AN ANALYSIS OF THE LOOK-UP TABLE    FW
)@@G@@@G@@@6C     0100  DO NOT SORT.  PRINT FILES AS THEY OCCUR IN THE DIRECTOFX
)@@G@@RY    @F@@@6C     0200  DO NOT LIST ANY FILES.  PRINT ONLY SUMMARY INFORFY
)@@G@@MATION@G@@@6C     0400  ANALYZE THE SIZE OF FILES WHICH HAVE BEEN BACKEDFZ
)@@G@@ UP WITHIN  @G@@@6C           24 HRS AND PACK AS NECESSARY.  DO NO UPDATGA
)@@G@@E THE TLR FOR ANY @#@@@6C           FILE. % @@@@-28,28       MAIN/LISTFIGB
)@@G@@LES   @F@'@6C     1000  ASSIGN AND FREE ALL FILES WITHUPT OUDATING THEIRGC
)@@G@@ TLR. @F@@['C     1000  ASSIGN AND FREE ALL FILES WITHOUT UPDATING THEIRGD
)@@G@@ TLR. @F@9@6C     1010  ASSIGN ALL FILES WHICH NEED TO BE TRANSLATED FROGE
)@@G@@M DADS@F@9@6C           TO GRANULE TABLES.  (EXEC 33 TO EXEC 32 CONVERSIGF
)@@G@@ON)   %@@@@[@F[@@6C     2000  ANALYZE THE SIZE OF ALL MASS STORAGE FILESGG
)@@G@@ AND PACK AS@F@@@6C           NECESSARY.  DO NOT UPDATE THE TLR STAMP FOGH
)@@G@@R ANY FILE. @B@9@6C           THEIR TIME OF LAST REFERENCE. @[@@@6C     GI
)@@G@@@[@@@6C     @D@@@6C           OPTION LETTERS CONTROLLING FILE LISTING   GJ
)@@G@@@G@@@6C     A     PROCESS FILES WHOSE ACCOUNT NUMBER MATCHES THE FIRST SGK
)@@G@@IX    % @@@@-35,35       MAIN/LISTFILES   @G@'@6C           DIGITS OF THGL
)@@G@@E USER'S ACCOUNT.  (MUST ALSO HAVE U OPTION ON) @F@@['C           DIGITSGM

)@@G@@OPERATE IN TEST MODE (USE THE ACCOUNT NUMBER HARD CODED     @G@@@6C     GO
